title: strawberry crumble cake
directions: Layer strawberries in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Spread pineapple over strawberries. Sprinkle cake mix over mixture and cut butter over cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes, then let cool and put Cool Whip on top.

title: apple baked beans
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add cubed apples and cook until tender.
Add brown sugar and white sugar.
Stir and cook until sugar is melted.
Stir in cinnamon, catsup, molasses and salt. Add beans and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400°
for 30 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake another 30 minutes.

title: pizza salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients, mixing gently but thoroughly.
Cover; chill 4 hours or overnight.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine crushed crackers, melted oleo and 2 tablespoons sugar together and line bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex.
Save enough crumbs to sprinkle on top.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until done.
Debone.
Mix chicken, broth and soup together.
Place into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add drained Veg-All.
Mix flour, milk and margarine together and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain water.
Place half the macaroni in ungreased baking dish.
Slice half the butter.
Lay over macaroni. Slice half of the cheese and lay over the macaroni.
Add 1/2 cup of milk.
Add a small portion of salt and pepper.
Repeat all ingredients.
Heat oven to 375°.
Cover and bake 30 minutes. Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Salt and pepper and pour over cooked carrots, bell pepper and onion; toss slightly and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Serves 6 to 8.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Trim dark green and pink parts from rind; cut in 1-inch squares.
Measure 6 cups.
Soak overnight in solution of salt and 1-quart water (it may take more).
Drain; rinse rind; cover with cold water.
Cook abuut 25 minutes or until just tender.

title: apple cake with walnuts
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, sugar and cinnamon in large bowl; mix well.
Beat vanilla, oil and eggs in small mixer bowl until foamy.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: lime-lemon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Pour into 8 x 12 1/2-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Coat fish fillet with this layer of mayonnaise.
Season with salt and lemon pepper.
Roll in crushed cracker crumbs.
Place in shallow pan, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 400° until flaky.

title: fresh corn relish
directions: Toss together corn, bell pepper, onion, oil and vinegar in a medium bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hamburger-cornbread casserole
directions: In a large iron skillet, cook meat, onions and bell pepper. Stir in corn, mashed potatoes, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Press down in skillet.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.

title: "marinade for smoked goose or turkey"
directions: Drain. Soak 12 hours. Bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and saute until golden.
Add corn, milk, crumbs, eggs and a little salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine ingredients in order. Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chocolate bag
directions: You will also need a lacy paper doily and 2-inch paper bag.

title: pie crust(easy)
directions: Combine salt and flour.
Mix in shortening and butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk, mixing until dough forms.
Knead dough, forming it into a ball.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Place pared, cut apples in a large bowl.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and nutmeg in a cup, then sprinkle over apples to cover top.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour in a small bowl.
Cut in butter, then sprinkle over apples to cover top.
Slide pie into a heavy brown paper bag, large enough to cover pie loosely.
Fold open end over twice and fasten with paper clips.
Place in hot oven (425°) and bake 1 hour.
Slit bag open and cool on wire rack.

title: hash brown potato bake
directions: Spread potatoes in 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with onions, salt and pepper.
Mix soup, cream cheese, milk and butter.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on (in the last 5 minutes of baking). Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice and sausage quick dish
directions: Slice sausage into bite size pieces.
Add other ingredients into covered casserole dish.
Mix well.
Cook about 1 hour at 350°.

title: creole
directions: Chop steak into thin 2-inch long strips.
Fry steak in grease until browned.
Drain grease.
Place steak in deep fryer or large frying pan.
(No grease.)
Peel and slice potatoes.
Place them on top of the steak.
Peel, slice and tear apart onions.
Place on top of potatoes, slice carrots and place on top of onions.
Pour 1 can of tomato soup and 1 can water over top (more water may be needed).
Cover.
Let cook on medium heat for approximately 2 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a small mixing bowl. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and sour cream.
Fold chicken into mixture.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: ranch soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and taco mixture.
Add other ingredients and simmer. Freezes well.

title: potato pizza
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add cheese soup and milk; heat and mix. Cover bottom of pan with potatoes; pour hamburger mixture over potatoes.
Mix together the tomato soup, chopped onion, oregano, pepper and sugar.
Spread this over hamburger mixture.
Put sliced pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are cooked.
Melt cheese on top.

title: fruit and nut cake
directions: Combine walnuts, dates, raisins and baking soda.
Add boiling water and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil in mixing bowl.
Add flour, then eggs, one at a time, blending well.
Add vanilla and lemon rind.
Stir in fruit and nut mixture.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: lima bean salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard and salt in a 1 1/2-quart bowl; toss with remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours. Refrigerate any leftover salad immediately.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli.
Melt margarine and add flour; blend well.
Add milk slowly; bring to a boil.
Add cheese slowly (don't boil). Add broccoli.

title: chess pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour and nutmeg together.
Add to beaten eggs. Add meal and vinegar.
Melt butter or margarine slightly and add. Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: buttery pasta with shrimp
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat (5 to 7 minutes).
Add all ingredients except tomatoes and cheese.
Saute 5 to 7 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti; stir to blend.
Continue cooking over medium heat.
Stir occasionally until heated (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove from heat; add tomatoes; cover and let stand 1 minute or until tomatoes are heated.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Serves six (1 1/2 cups each).
When preparing shrimp, you will have to cook in boiling water for 10 minutes prior to adding to other ingredients.

title: peaches 'n cream dessert bars
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, 2 eggs, butter and dry frosting mix.
By hand, stir until cake is moistened.
Press in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: shrimp curry with rice
directions: Cook onions, garlic and ginger in butter until lightly browned.
Add curry, flour, salt and pepper and blend.
Add chicken broth gradually and cook and stir until thick.
Add shrimp.
Serve
over rice.
Serves 4.

title: wedding brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa; add to eggs and sugar and mix.
Then add salt, flour and baking powder.
Mix together and put in greased dripper pan.
Bake at 370° for 27 minutes.

title: guacamole saladlubbock, texas
directions: Mix everything by blending or mixing.
Put the tomato, cut in wedges, on top of the salad.

title: no-bake rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water and salt at medium heat until all the water is absorbed.
Add milk, vanilla and sugar until desired consistency (a little softer than you want to end up with).
Add egg and raisins and cook for 4 to 5 minutes longer.
Great served warm or cold!

title: carl's beans
directions: Start the night before you cook beans. Clean beans thoroughly, getting all the rocks and dirt out of them.
I don't like doing this part so I get Claudia to do this.
After beans are cleaned, soak overnight in water.
After the chicken crows and you've had a couple cups of coffee, put beans and water they soaked in all night in a pan large enough to hold it all.
Put on stove and light fire. Add ham hocks and cubed ham at this time.

If you have an electric roaster, cook in this; that's what I prefer. Cook beans all day, stirring occasionally, and adding water as needed. Now these beans will be fit for supper with your favorite cornbread and some fried taters and onions.
And don't forget some sliced fresh onions.
Yum! Yum!

title: soap bubbles
directions: Mix ingredients and use immediately.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Stir in sour cream and half of Cool Whip in large pan.
Place a layer of wafers on bottom, top with bananas and pudding mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and chill for a few hours.
It is better to prepare a day ahead.

title: island cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, pineapple, bell pepper, onion, salt and 1 cup of the pecans.
Chill.
Shape into 2 balls and roll in remaining pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mom's yorkshire pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs slightly with egg beater; beat in 1 cup milk.
Sift and measure 1 cup all-purpose flour.
Resift into milk-egg mixture with salt.
Beat until smooth.
Measure 1/2 cup hot drippings form roasting 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour pudding batter into pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with roast beef and gravy.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Boil chicken until tender with enough water to make stock for dumplins (approximately 2 quarts).
Debone chicken and reserve separate from broth.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Add enough cold water to make dough with consistency to roll out.
In small portions, roll out between wax paper with generous additional amount of flour.
Cut in 2-inch strips.
Add gradually to slow boiling broth, stretching and breaking into 2 or 3-inch pieces. Use fork and push dumplin over to make room in juice to cook next piece.
Continue until all is used, shaking cooker occasionally to keep from sticking, until done.
Add margarine and milk.
Reheat. Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: To bake in the old-fashioned way;

title: orange peanut refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt, set aside.

Cream together butter with sugars. Beat in egg. Blend in undeluted orange concentrate, orange rind and dry ingredients. Stir in peanuts. Chill dough. Shape into 2 rolls, 2 inches in diameter. Wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Cut into 1\4 inch slices. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400 ° for 10 to 12 min. or until lightly browned. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix
and
pour	into
greased 9 x 13-inch pan.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed rolled chicken breasts
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add bouillon, hot water and stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Lightly pound chicken breasts so they lay flat.
Place some stuffing on each breast and roll up around stuffing.
Place breasts, seam side down, in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place remaining stuffing along side of breasts.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Mix well and pour over rolled breast.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover tightly.
Bake about 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut each unpeeled potato into 8 wedges. Arrange wedges, peel side down, in 2 shallow baking pans. Combine remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Brush oil mix over potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender, brushing occasionally with oil mixture.
Serves 8.

title: baked beans
directions: In skillet, lightly brown hot dogs and onion in butter and spices.
Add beans, catsup, mustard and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into casserole and bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine corn, eggs, muffin mix and sour cream.
Add cooled, melted butter, salt and pepper. Pour into greased 10-inch square casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and return to oven for 15 additional minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Butter 13 x 9 inch pan, layer with doritos followed by chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tex mex
directions: Spread bean dip on bottom of platter.
Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning together.
Spread on top of bean dip, then spread on avocado dip.
Sprinkle on onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and oregano.
Stir and cook for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.

title: "best in the west" barbecue bean bake
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Drain.
Combine all other ingredients EXCEPT the beans.
Stir in meat mixture.
Add beans and stir thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or cook in crock-pot on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Make into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, then molasses and coffee (instant coffee made double strength is good).
Add one cup flour and
rest
of
dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add remaining flour.
Form
into balls the size of a walnut, using flour to prevent
sticking.	Place on a greased cookie sheet, flatten slightly,
and
bake in a 350° oven until light brown, but still soft
in
the center.
Cool on rack or brown paper. Makes about 5 dozen medium large cookies.

title: maple syrup
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, let boil 7 minutes or until desired thickness.
Add flavorings and butter after cooled 15 minutes if desired.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In a 10-inch skillet cook zucchini and onion until tender in oleo (about 10 minutes).
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend in eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture. Separate crescent rolls and put into 10-inch pie plate.
Press in bottom and sides.
Spread with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture evenly into crust.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.
If crust becomes too brown, cover with foil the last 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Also good cold.

title: cheeseburger pockets
directions: In a skillet, cook beef, onion, salt and pepper over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain and cool. Place 2 biscuits overlapping on a floured surface. Roll out into 5-inch oval. Place 3 tablespoons meat mixture on one side. Fold a cheese slice to fit over meat mixture. Fold dough over filling. Press edges with a fork to seal. Repeat with remaining biscuits, meat mixture and cheese. Place on a greased baking sheet. Prick tops with a fork. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 5 servings.

title: english muffin appetizers
directions: Preheat oven broiler to 400°.
In medium bowl, stir together first six ingredients until smooth.
Stir in black olives and cheese.
Spread 2 tablespoons of mixture on each muffin half, then cut into quarters.
Broil 1 inch apart on cookie sheet until top is bubbly and cheese is melted, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Watch closely.
Remove from oven and serve immediately.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add the egg and beat.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Crush 4 candy bars.
Mix with 1/2 cup nuts.
Add to batter and stir.
Pour into a greased sheet cake pan.
Crush the other 4 candy bars.
Mix with the other 1/2 cup nuts.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until it tests done.

title: calico apple salad
directions: Combine peanut butter and honey; gradually add milk.
Add Miracle Whip; mix well.
Chill. Combine fruit and celery.
Toss with salad dressing mixture to coat.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: apple rings
directions: Soak cucumbers in solution of
1 cup pickling lime to 1 gallon of water for 24
hours.
Rinse
and soak in clear water for 3 hours;
drain and rinse again.
Simmer rings in solution of 1 cup vinegar, 1 cup water, alum and red food color; do not boil.
Drain and cover with syrup mixture of 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, cinnamon and red hot candies; bring to boil until red hots melt.
Drain
rings
and
cover with syrup mixture, boiling hot. Pack rings in jar and seal.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well, and rinse in cold water.
At least 2 hours before serving, marinate beans in rest of ingredients.
Serve plain or on lettuce leaf.
This mixture is even better if made the day before it is to be served.

title: my grandma's penuche
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to a soft ball stage or 235°.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into an 8-inch pan.

title: thanksgiving salad
directions: Dissolve jello and let it start to set up.
Add pineapple, cranberry and nuts.

title: harvest loaves
directions: Stir apples and sugar together.
Let stand 1 hour.
Stir flour and spices together.
Beat eggs; add oil, vanilla and apples.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Divide between 2 sprayed loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: layered artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes; mix with diced chilies and line in bottom of dish.
Spread layer of mayonnaise over artichokes.
Cover with shredded Jack cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Serve hot with king-size Fritos.

title: caramels
directions: Place all ingredients in large pan.
Bring to boil and stir all the time.
When the mixture reaches 246° on a candy thermometer, pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan greased with butter. Mark in squares, wrap in waxed paper when cool.
You can dip in chocolate.
(Don't add the walnuts until just before you pour in buttered dish.)

title: breaded green beans
directions: In medium saucepan, heat green beans until very hot.
Remove from heat and drain. Add margarine and bread crumbs.
Mix until beans are evenly coated.
Serve with your favorite meat, poultry or fish.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Whip cream until it holds its shape.
Add eggs and whip until light as foam.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to egg mixture. Bake in greased layer cake pans in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes two 8-inch layers.
Cool and spread with your favorite icing or whipped cream between the layers and on top.

title: party fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread onto a serving plate.
Layer cheese mixture with caramel.
Layer caramel with pecans.
Arrange fruit slices around dip mixture.

title: sour cream and herb dressing
directions: Mash yolks in bowl.
Add sour cream.
Mix well, then press mixture through a sieve.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and fresh chopped herbs.
Chill.
Great on sliced cucumbers and tomatoes.

title: chow chow
directions: Put cabbage, onions, green peppers, tomatoes and red peppers in alternate layers in an enamel pan.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and top with a complete covering of salt.
Let stand 12 hours. Drain.
Put vinegar, sugar, mustard, mustard seed and celery seed in enamel kettle.
Tie cloves in cheesecloth and add to mixture. Bring to boiling point, add vegetable mixture and simmer slowly until all are tender, about 1/2 hour.
Remove cloves; pack mixture into hot clear jar.
Seal at once.

title: scalloped clams
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Recipe may be cut in half.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill large container of a pressure cooker halfway with water; add Old Bay.
Bring to a boil; add potatoes.
Return to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn.
Return to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Remove with a slotted spoon onto a large platter or newspaper lined table.
Serve with additional Old Bay and cocktail sauce.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll out by hand or biscuit cutter. Grease pan thoroughly.
Place biscuits in pan.
Bake at 500° until brown.

title: creamy parmesan polenta
directions: Combine water and cornmeal in small bowl.
Bring broth to boil in heavy saucepan, gradually add cornmeal mixture, stirring until well blended.
Reduce heat to low until polenta is very thick, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. Mix in 1/2 cup cheese, cream and butter.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.

title: squash casserole quiche
directions: Steam squash and onion.
Mash.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in covered, lightly
greased casserole dish for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.
Store in tightly sealed container.
Serve
teaspoon in 1 cup boiling water.
Also good served over ice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt butter in a pan.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute until golden.
Let cool.
Dice bread and soak in milk.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook in pan juice from pineapple, flour, sugar, egg and vinegar until thick, about 10 to 15 minutes; cool.	Add to Cool Whip and pour over apples, pineapple and marshmallows; nuts may be added.
Mix well and chill.
I use Spanish cocktail peanuts for the nuts.
Tastes like a taffy apple.
Best if made the day before and nuts added a couple of hours before serving.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pick off bone.
Cook broccoli.
Mix mushroom soup, Miracle Whip and lemon juice.
Then layer in greased baking dish broccoli and chicken.
Pour sauce mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese or Cheez Whiz and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Also can cook rice and pour mixture over.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel and dice the eggplant.
Boil eggplant until it is tender enough to mash.
Cool, then add egg and stir.
Then add salt to taste.
Add sugar.
Add baking powder and then add enough flour to make dough thick enough to spoon.
Heat oil until it is really hot and spoon dough into oil; let fry until brown.
Serve hot.

title: sausage pasta supper
directions: Stir-fry the following into butter until crisp.
Add onions, peppers, mushrooms, vegetables, garlic, oregano and sausage, cut into bite size pieces.
Heat through.
Stir in Parmesan cheese. Serve over buttered pasta with additional cheese.

title: apple puffs
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Add sugar and apples. Mix to a stiff batter with egg and milk. Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease and cook until the puffs are golden brown. Drain and serve.

title: french lace cookie
directions: Sift flour.
Blend flour and nuts.
Bring syrup, butter, and sugar to boil in pan over medium heat; gradually stir in flour and nuts.
Drop batter by level teaspoon full about 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 or 9 cookies at a time.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Let set a little before taking off cookie sheet.

title: bean pie
directions: Mix beans, cooked and run through a colander the milk, sugar, 2 well beaten eggs, butter, vanilla and a dash of nutmeg together. Bake in pie shell as you would a potato pie.

title: fruit chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add mayonnaise and apples. Season with salt and pepper.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: zucchini tomato casserole
directions: Place
carrots, onions and tomatoes in a 2 quart casserole dish.
Add chicken hot dogs and arrange evenly.
Sprinkle on salt,
pepper and chili powder.
Layer the zucchini, overlapping and
filling the dish.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: "light" blueberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using the two substitutes.
Bake and let cool completely (3 or 4 layers).
Mix sugars and cream cheese together by hand.
Add Cool Whip lite and mix with mixer.

title: enchilada acapulco chicken
directions: Make the filling by combining the chicken, olives and almonds, adding 1/3 cup of the sauce to moisten.

title: oklahoma brown candy
directions: Measure 2 cups sugar into a heavy skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring with wooden spoon as it melts and becomes a syrup, about the color of light brown sugar (don't burn it!).

Mix the other 4 cups of sugar and the lite cream into a large, deep, heavy kettle. Over low heat, bring to a boil, then increase heat to a fast boil. Pour the melted sugar from the skillet into the large kettle mixture in a small, thin stream, stirring continuously to blend. Cook and stir mixture until it reaches a firm ball stage (244° to 248°).
Remove from heat.
Add soda and stir vigorously as it foams.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Set aside at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until candy becomes thick and the glossy appearance turns dull.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into a buttered 11 x 9-inch dish.

title: fruit pizza(dessert)
directions: Slice cookie dough thinly and overlap on pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool.

title: snow peak frosting
directions: In small saucepan over medium heat, heat corn syrup until boiling.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt; continue beating just until soft peaks form.
Slowly pour in hot syrup, continuing to beat for 6 to 8 minutes until frosting is fluffy and forms peaks when beater is raised.
Beat in vanilla.

title: pizza party dip
directions: Spread cream cheese onto pizza pan.
Spread on cocktail sauce. Sprinkle on shrimp and cheese.
Cool in refrigerator and serve with Fritos, tortillas or crackers.

title: microwave nippy cheese broccoli
directions: Place broccoli, icy side up, in 2-quart utility dish. Alternate spears and florets.*
Place margarine, flour and salt in 2 cup measure.
Mix and slowly stir in milk.
Place in oven and heat 3 to 4 minutes on High power, stirring every minute or until mixture thickens.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Pour cheese sauce down center of dish over broccoli.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Return to oven and heat 1 to 2 minutes to warm tomatoes.

title: hamburger dinner casserole
directions: Fry hamburger in 6 thin patties.
Brown on both sides.
Put patties in bottom of oblong casserole dish.
Pour bean juice into hamburger frying pan and bring just to a boil.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet; add onion, garlic and thyme. Saute over medium heat until onion is tender (about 10 minutes). Transfer to bowl and set aside.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: Cook syrup, sugar, salt and water together, without stirring, to 250° or until a small amount dropped into cold water will form a firm ball.
Pour the hot syrup over beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and continue beating until frosting is cool and thick enough to spread.
Add marshmallows, cut into eighths.
Will cover tops and sides of 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: sausage and cornbread casserole
directions: Cook sausage and onion in large skillet over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble. Drain the grease. Add tomatoes, chilies, corn and chili
powder, simmering 20 minutes.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Mix ground chuck, beans, sour cream, raw onion, 1/2 green onions, 1/3 Cheddar cheese and 1/3 tomato.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in casserole and add broth.
Cover with layers of egg slices and then add chicken.
Pour soup over this and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat 12 minutes, stirring constantly. Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Stir until cool and thick enough to spread.

title: stove top potpourri
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store airtight at room temperature.

title: green beans in cheese sauce
directions: Combine cheese, milk, pimento, Worcestershire sauce, salt and cayenne in double boiler.
Cook over boiling water until sauce is smooth.
May be cooked in microwave.
Crumble bacon.
Mix with bread crumbs tossed with a little margarine.
Place beans in greased pan.
Cover with bacon-bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until top is golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: In pan, saute oleo, green peppers and onions.
Cook 2 minutes. Add soup, undiluted; set aside.
In casserole dish, put layer of noodles (1/2), then 1/2 of chicken, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of soup. Repeat layers.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hard christmas candy
directions: Stir until boils.
Do not stir until candy reaches 310° on a candy thermometer.
Add 1 oil flavoring and desired color.
Pour on bed of powdered sugar.
Cut with scissors when becomes cool enough to do so.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Combine and mix well.
Add paprika and biscuit mix.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be baked, frozen and reheated.

title: flavored bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine first six (6) ingredients; stir well. Combine pumpkin (or banana or apple) and next three (3) ingredients; mix well.
Add these to dry ingredients, stir just until moist.
Spoon into muffin pans (coated with spray).
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Check at 18 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.
Good served warm or cool.
Yields 1 dozen (12) muffins.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well, reserving 1 cup of the liquid.
Set aside.

title: mexican meat dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet. Drain. Place meat and onions in slow cooker. Add beans and taco seasoning mix. Mix together well. Spread sour cream over mixture. Sprinkle cheese over top. Cover. Cook on low 1 1/2 hours or on high 3/4 hour. Serve warm from the cooker with tortilla chips.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter together, then add remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Put in large bowl and layer lettuce, onion, celery, eggs, water chestnuts and bacon.
Cover and seal with mayonnaise. Sprinkle Parmesan over top.
Put Saran Wrap over all and refrigerate overnight.
Stir well.

title: broccoli casserole #1
directions: Mix broccoli (cooked or raw), eggs, mushrooms, Miracle Whip and mushroom soup. Pour in casserole pan. Sprinkle Ritz crackers and cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Put cloves and allspice in a metal tea ball or tie them in a cheesecloth bag for easy removal.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together everything but the eggs and oil.
Beat eggs and oil.
Pour over mixture, stir until well moistened.
Turn into greased and floured bread pan and bake at 350 degrees for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: stir-fried liver with sherry
directions: Saute celery
and onion in corn oil.
Stir in liver and sherry,
cooking 3 to 5 minutes.
Avoid overcooking.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: country apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and 1 egg at low speed until crumbly.
Press in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with pie filling.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Pour half the batter into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chiles and half the cheese.
Pour on remaining batter.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting into serving pieces.

title: seafood gumbo(serves 12 generously)
directions: Make a roux of flour and bacon drippings in a heavy iron pot. Cook over medium heat and stir constantly until a rich brown color.
Add 1 heaping tablespoonful of fresh ground file right before you remove roux from heat, stirring constantly, until roux and file are well blended.
Then to the roux and file
mixture, add garlic, celery and onions.
Cook over low heat for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring often until greens are wilted.
If using okra, fresh or frozen, cook in a small amount of fat in a separate skillet until all the "string" is gone.
Add okra to greens and cook together, about 10 minutes.
Add chicken stock and hot water. Season to taste with salt, black and red pepper.
Simmer slowly for about 1 hour.
Add shrimp and crabmeat.
Simmer slowly about 30 minutes.
Add oysters and juice; cook about 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Add 3 tablespoons fresh file and serve over hot rice.

title: date muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl; make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add 3/4 cup coarsely chopped dates.
Stir quickly into batter.
Fill greased muffin pans or paper bake cups 2/3 full. Bake about 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients into the corn meal.
Mix everything together and pour into a lightly greased glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: wild rice stuffed turkey
directions: For stuffing, prepare rice mix according to package directions.
In a 12-inch skillet cook and stir bacon, onion and garlic in hot margarine or butter, about 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a jelly roll pan 15 X 10 1/2 inch.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto batter.
Cut through batter with knife or metal spatula several times for marbled effect.
Sprinkle with additional chocolate chips and chopped nuts if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding milk last.
Pour into baking dish, buttered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake, oranges and juice, eggs and oil all together.
Pour in Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: 10-minute tomato soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, heat tomatoes until boiling. Remove from the heat. Add remaining ingredients. Return to heat and cook on medium until butter is melted and the soup is heated through. Yields 1 quart.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Cut baked potatoes in half and scoop out potatoes from shell. Mash potatoes and remaining ingredients.
Refill shells with mashed potatoes and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: poor man's lobster no. 1
directions: Place fish into boiling water.
Mix and boil until fish flakes easily.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs; add rest of ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown together meat and onion.
Add Veg-All, tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes (I run both tomatoes through blender).
Add Spanish rice and creamed corn last; cook slowly and stir often. Corn will stick if cooked too fast!

title: english walnut fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add slowly to first mixture and beat well.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: better than *** pie
directions: Mix all but last ingredient.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together and pour into baked crust. Bake another 25 minutes. When cooled, slightly sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Bake the potatoes until tender.
Peel and shred into a large bowl.
Turn into a 2-quart greased casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Set out one hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jiffy oatmeal cookies
directions: Save some powdered sugar to roll balls of cookie in.
Cream butter with powdered sugar.
Add cocoa, vanilla, water and oatmeal. Mold into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: lime ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple with syrup and cold water.
Chill until mixture mounds from a spoon. Stir in evaporated milk, marshmallows and coconut.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: apple cinnamon salad
directions: Dissolve cinnamon candies in hot water.
Dissolve jello in hot water; combine when partly set.
Add chopped apples, celery and nuts.

title: shrimp in jackets
directions: Thaw the shrimp.
Sprinkle with garlic or onion salt.
Cut bacon in thirds.
Wrap each shrimp in 1/3 slice bacon.
Arrange on broiler rack.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat, just until bacon is crisp and browned (8 to 10 minutes); turn occasionally.
Serve on cocktail picks.
Makes about 40.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core head of cabbage.
Place into pot of boiling water.
As leaves wilt, remove them.
You may wish to slice down heavier leaf spines.
Cook rice in 1 cup of water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place cut up chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan, seasoned with salt, pepper and Tony Chachere seasoning and bake at 350° until done. While chicken is baking, cook rice.
After chicken and rice are done, debone and remove skin from chicken; mix all ingredients together.
Season with salt and red pepper to taste.
If mixture is too dry, add a little chicken broth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake until cheese is melted and slightly golden brown on top. This is a delicious meal.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain
artichokes well, then place on a paper towel and press out excess juice.
Chop fine.
Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, garlic and artichokes.
Spray
shallow
glass
baking dish with Pam and spread mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve on crackers.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and shape into small meatballs.
Put in skillet and cook on medium while you are mixing remaining ingredients in a bowl for your sauce.
Meatballs will be almost fully cooked, but idea is to get excess fat off before being baked in a baking dish with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and okra
directions: In a
large pot, put wings, 1 onion, salt, 1 can tomato sauce, red
pepper, black or white pepper and enough water to cover wings.
Cook
slowly.
Saute sausage to extract grease; don't brown.
Set aside.	Clean and devein shrimp;
set aside. In a large
skillet,
put bacon fat.
Heat, then add okra and onions. Saute
until okra is half done.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic
powder and seasoned salt. Mix with chicken and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add sausage and shrimp and cook for 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: horseradish ring
directions: Beat eggs and mix with vinegar, sugar and horseradish.
Soak and melt gelatine over hot water.
Add gelatine to egg mixture in double boiler and cook until creamy.
Cool over cold water.
Fold in stiffly beaten whipped cream.
Pour into ring mold.
Serves 8.

title: uncertain for eight
directions: Cook rice as directed; add a little salt.
When rice is cooked, put in a casserole.
Add tomatoes and mix.
Dice cheese over this mixture and bake in 300° oven for 15 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake sugar cookie mix in pizza pan and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and put over crust.
Top with desired fruit.
If desired, you can melt 1/3 cup orange marmalade or apple jelly and pour over fruit.

title: virginia's sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potato; drain well.
Add oleo; beat with mixer.
Add sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla and beat with mixer.
Pour into two uncooked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until firm.

title: goody bars
directions: Melt all ingredients together.
Spread on a cookie sheet. Chill and cut.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together (save 1/4 of cheese for top). Pour into greased baking dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. May add 2 cups cooked, chopped chicken to mixture.

title: broccoli cole slaw
directions: Prepare noodles according to directions on package. Save packs of spices for dressing. Let cool. Add other ingredients and mix. Refrigerate.

title: pineapple magic
directions: Put pineapple chunks in a bowl.
Put it in the freezer for 3 to 4 hours.
Take it out when it is ready.
Then put in the blender.
Serve immediately.

title: stuffed cinnamon apples
directions: Pare and core apples.
Cook candies in water until dissolved. Add apples and cook slowly, uncovered, until just tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn once during cooking.
Chill apples in syrup; turn once during chilling.

title: deer sausage in sauce
directions: Cut deer sausage roll in thick pieces and then quarter the pieces.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix the rest of ingredients and pour over deer meat.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
This is a favorite for gathering of family and friends.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Drain and rinse spaghetti. Grease bowl or casserole pan.
Place rest of ingredients in layered form as follows:
spaghetti, whole peeled tomatoes, tomato sauce, sliced Colby Longhorn cheese and sprinkle salt and pepper for flavor.
Keep layering until you top with tomato sauce and salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 10 servings.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Make cake mix as directed.
Mix cheese, egg and sugar together.
In paper lined cupcake pan fill 3/4 full with cake mix. Drop 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Frost with icing.

title: chicken and sherry casserole
directions: Mix flour, paprika and marjoram and roll chicken pieces in same.
Brown chicken on both sides in butter or oil.
Dilute mushroom soup with sherry.
Add mushroom pieces.
Place browned chicken in covered casserole; pour soup and sherry mixture over same.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Good served over rice or noodles or with biscuits.
May be assembled to baking point and refrigerated overnight.
Bring to room temperature, then bake for 1 hour.

title: bacon tater bites
directions: Preheat oven to bake at 425°.
Open package of Tater Tots and empty them onto the bottom pan of the broiler pan.
Place the pan of Tots on the middle shelf of the oven.
Set the timer and cook the Tater Tots 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar with apples and let stand for 2 hours.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Place lettuce, peas, cauliflower, cucumber and pepper in large flat container.
Top with onion slices and crumbled bacon bits. Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan and top salad with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar in saucepan until thick.
Put in fridge to cool several hours.
Add apples, peanuts (crushed in blender) and Cool Whip.

title: oven-cooked round steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt and pepper and dredge steak in flour.
Heat margarine in ovenproof skillet. Saute garlic until golden, move to one side.
Brown meat on both sides.
Pour milk over the meat and sprinkle with herbs.
Place skillet in oven and bake until meat is quite tender and milk has formed gravy.
Serve immediately.

title: festive fudge
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil; set aside. In medium-sized heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with Eagle Brand and salt. Remove from heat; stir in nuts, if desired, and the vanilla. Spread evenly into pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm. Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off foil and cut into squares. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, salt and water. Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to 285°, stirring frequently.
Add peanuts and continue cooking until thermometer reaches 295°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Work fast.
Pour into 2 greased pans.
Spread quickly as thin as possible for extra brittleness.

title: marshmallow coconut cookies
directions: Combine sugar,	margarine
and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove
from heat and add marshmallow cream and vanilla; beat until melted.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and pecans.
Mix well
and
pour
into
pan.
Cut
in squares when cool.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni using package directions.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine with next 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well. Add mixture of mayonnaise and curry powder; mix lightly.

title: hooligan's fudge
directions: Melt together oleo and cheese (can use microwave).
Stir in cocoa, vanilla, sugar and nuts.
Press into lightly greased pan. Store in cool place.
Makes 3 pounds fudge.

title: french onion soup
directions: Stir ingredients together and drop from teaspoon into not boiling soup the last 15 minutes of cooking.
When Klimpers are done, they will come to the top.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 4 minutes. Take off heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool. Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: divinity
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, water and salt. Bring to boil; boil to soft ball stage, stirring while sugar melts to keep from burning. Pour over marshmallow cream and vanilla in large bowl. Beat 1 minute. Add nuts and stir gently until mixed well. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: mother's mud cookies
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Cook until it comes to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes; take off stove.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on a buttered tinfoil or wax paper.

title: casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole and bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered.
Last 15 minutes, cover with Chinese noodles.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs together.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fudge frosting
directions: In a heavy medium sized saucepan, combine the sugar and cream. Place over medium heat and stirring constantly, bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes without stirring.
Remove from the heat and stir in the chocolate, butter or margarine and vanilla.
Continue stirring until chocolate and butter melt.
Turn into a bowl and cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally. Refrigerate, stirring frequently, until thickened and of a good spreading consistency.

title: janet's white sauce(microwave)
directions: Microwave on High the butter in custard cup.
Blend in the flour and salt.
Heat milk in 1-quart measuring cup for 2 minutes and 30 seconds until almost boiling.
Beat in paste.
Microwave 2 minutes on #8 until thick.
Stir after one minute.

title: easy spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white slightly; add water.
Beat until frothy, but not stiff.
Pour over pecans in a large bowl, stirring until nuts are coated.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over pecans; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir once or twice while baking.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: honey cake(low-fat)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend together oil, honey and egg whites.
In separate bowl, stir flour and dry ingredients together.
Add flour mixture and apple juice together all at once to honey mixture.
Stir until the dry ingredients are just moistened.
Fold in raisins if desired.
Spoon batter into lightly oiled (or sprayed)
9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.

title: burger melt
directions: Shape ground beef into 6 patties.
Brown in large skillet. Drain grease.
Add tomato soup and about 1/3 cup water.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes or until patties are no longer pink.
Top with cheese and serve on buns.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Spread macaroni in a 9 x 13-inch pan; then spread sour cream and cream cheese.
Then spread meat with sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Put yeast in water; let stand 5 minutes.
Put scalded milk in large bowl with honey, butter and salt.
Stir until butter melts. Add 2 cups flour and oats.
Stir and cool (lukewarm).
Add yeast and mix well.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead 10 minutes.
Put in
greased bowl.
Cover and rise until doubled. Punch down.
Put in 2 loaf pans.
Rise.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon whippersnaps(quick, easy and good)
directions: Combine mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Drop by spoonful into powdered sugar.
Flatten with a glass bottom onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: "puffy" sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into balls, then roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: asparagus and ham roll-ups
directions: Place 3 to 4 asparagus spears on each ham slice.
Roll up like jelly roll and secure with toothpick.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook and stir until thick and pasty.
Add milk and stir until thickened.
Add cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Place rolls in heatproof baking dish. Pour cheese sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave 80% power for 7 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in a heavy skillet.
Beat egg yolks slightly and combine with sugar very slowly.
Cook over medium heat until the sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add grated cheese, sugar and mustard.
Mix well. Add cooked macaroni and margarine.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt brigie's irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Rub shortening into dry ingredients.
Mix eggs and buttermilk and add to flour mixture, stirring well.
Add raisins and mix well.
Place in an ovenproof skillet or a 9-inch round cake pan (greased), spreading dough to fill pan.
Cut a cross in the top of the dough to prevent cracking.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Do not preheat oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix
together
sugar,
Crisco,	butter, and your 6 eggs. Add flour,
salt, baking powder, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: thirteen vegetable soup
directions: Brown the chuck roast.
Save bones.
Bring water to a boil. On top of meat add Wyler's.
Add the onion, tomatoes, leeks and celery and cook for 2 hours.
Add turnips, cabbage, carrots and potatoes and cook for 30 minutes.
Add beans, lima beans, corn, okra and peas and cook for another 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese and dill dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender except raw vegetables.
Blend until smooth.
Chill, covered, for at least 1 hour before serving with raw vegetables.
Makes 8 (2 tablespoon) servings; 35 cal. (12% from fat) per serving.

title: strawberry almond bars
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in butter. Press 2/3 of crumbs into 9-inch square (greased) pan.
Spread jam. Add almonds to remaining crumbs; sprinkle over jam.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: starch lover's special
directions: Place drained hamburger meat in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Pour the creamed corn on top of the hamburger and then spread creamed potatoes on top of corn.
Top with a pat of butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put into square or oblong dish.
Sprinkle with crushed cereal (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 generously.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook carrots in 1/2 inch boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Combine crackers, onion salt, green pepper and pepper.
Alternate layers of carrots and crumb mixture in greased 1-quart baking dish.
If any carrot liquid is left, spoon over the top.
Pour butter over and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Boil 1/4 cup water; mix Jell-O until dissolved. Mix in Cool Whip and Key lime yogurt. Chill and serve.

title: curried fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit, putting aside the nectars for possible future use. Arrange the fruit in a baking casserole, interspersing the raisins throughout. Combine the fruit, butter, lemon juice and curry powder thoroughly and pour this mixture over the fruit. Bake for an hour at 325°, then cover and refrigerate. The next day when the flavors have "married, " reheat and serve.

title: stove top stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic salt; drain and place in microwave-safe bowl.
In a large pot, cook noodles in olive oil according to directions, then drain.

Heat beef in microwave, then combine all ingredients, except milk, in pot on the stove top. Keep a low flame under pot until all ingredients are well mixed, then moisten to desired consistency with the milk.

title: egg nog pie
directions: A silver coin is hidden in this cake and at midnight a ceremony is held to begin the New Year.
The person who finds the coin in his slice will be blessed with good fortune and good health for the coming year.
The bread or cake baked for this occasion is in honor of St.
Basil on his nameday.
You may bake a bread or a cake as you desire.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare and cook cake as directed on mix.
Let cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip on top of cake; top with cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Fresh fruit can also be substituted for pie filling.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, squash and nuts.
Grease pan; sprinkle with flour.
Bake 1/2 hour to 1 hour (according to pan size) at 400°.

title: napoleon fruit juice
directions: Fill blender to top with ice.
Blend on high speed until slushy, then sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: chocolate pancakes
directions: Sift first 5 dry ingredients into large bowl.
Break eggs into another bowl.
Beat slightly.
Add the milk and stir.
Melt butter; set aside to cool.
Add egg mixture to the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in melted butter and chocolate chips.
Lightly grease a skillet.
Spoon batter in.
Serve with butter or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Nuts, raisins, chips, etc., can be added for variety.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spread mixture into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake uncovered at 425° for 10 minutes.
Combine biscuit mix, egg and milk to a soft dough.
Spoon over hot chicken mixture, bake uncovered at 425° for 20 - 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake 3 - 5 minutes more.

title: schnitz un knepp
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, melted butter and beaten egg. Using two spoons (spoons about the size of a large egg), put in broth.
Cook 10 minutes
uncovered, and 10 minutes covered.

title: apple salad
directions: Peel and cut apples into bite size pieces.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: crock-pot hamburger stew
directions: In bottom of crock-pot, place the hamburger, uncooked.
Layer in order the rice, onion, potato and carrot.
Mix the two soups together and pour over top, sealing the edges.
Cook on low, if started in the morning for dinner that night.

title: eggnog mallow fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Place sugar, marshmallows, eggnog, butter, corn syrup and salt in saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring, until marshmallows are melted.
Turn heat to medium and cook until mixture boils.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, to 230° on candy thermometer.
Add chocolate pieces and cook 5 minutes or until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill.
Cut into squares. Yield:
36 pieces.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Then fold in Cool Whip. Freeze in paper muffin tins cups.
Take out as wanted.
Will keep up to 6 months.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: I usually double recipe.

title: pfeffernuesse cookies
directions: Bring sugar, honey and Crisco to boil and cool.
Mix in order given.
Chill; shape into balls and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cookies are cooled, put into a container with a small amount of powdered sugar.
Shake to coat well.
This recipe can be halved easily.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in three 9 inch pans at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: such a salad
directions: Blend avocado, lemon juice, sour cream and seasonings to taste.
Shred lettuce into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and avocado dressing; toss.

title: noodles
directions: Add flour to make a very stiff dough.
Roll thin; let partially dry.
Cut into small short strips.
Dry.
Can be frozen and stored.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cut zucchini in half; peel and take out seeds.
Slice 4 cups and cover zucchini slices with boiling water.
Let set in warm water for 5 minutes.
Drain well (dry).
Add remaining ingredients to zucchini.
Mix all these ingredients well.
Put in pie shell. Dot with 2 tablespoons oleo and sprinkle 3 tablespoons lemon juice over.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Turn temperature down to 375° and continue baking for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef 'n cheese crescents
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and stir in barbecue sauce.
Set aside.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles on ungreased cookie sheet.
Overlap long sides and firmly press perforations and edges to seal.
Pat to form 15 x 13-inch rectangle.
Spread meat mixture lengthwise in 4-inch wide strip down center of dough to 1-inch from ends.
Top meat with cheese slices.
Fold shorter sides of dough over filling.
Bring long sides over, overlapping edges.
Pinch edges to seal.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with marshmallows.
Place in fridge until set.
Cook 1 cup pineapple juice, sugar and egg until thick.
Let cool. beat in cream cheese and pour over jello.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: sherbet punch
directions: In a punch bowl mix together sherbet and soft drink.
Stir occasionally until all the sherbet is melted.

title: butter coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in large bowl.
Add butter, egg, buttermilk, vanilla and 2/3 of coconut.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until set.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: canning sweet dill sticks
directions: Boil all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over cucumbers in sterile jars.
Process in boiling bath for 5 minutes for pints, 18 minutes for quarts.

title: french dressing with tomatoes
directions: In a jar or airtight container, place all ingredients, except cut tomatoes and lettuce leaves.
Shake well.
In a bowl, place tomatoes and enough dressing to cover.
Let stand several hours at room temperature.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream and baking powder.
On wax paper, sift baking soda and flour.
Add, alternating to batter, sour cream mixture and flour mixture.
If desired, layer cinnamon, sugar and/or nuts. Pour 1/2 batter and sprinkle remaining cinnamon, sugar and/or nuts. Pour balance of batter.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: favorite beef stew
directions: Brown beef slowly on all sides; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add liquid from green beans, 1 small bay leaf, 1/2 teaspoon thyme.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Add onions; simmer 30 minutes more.
Add potatoes and simmer until almost tender.
About 15 minutes before serving time, add green beans and tomatoes. Taste and correct seasoning before serving.

title: chicken roasted with basil and lemon
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a heavy baking dish combine the olive oil, garlic, salt and a grinding of pepper.
Rinse off the chicken breasts and pat dry; trim any fat.
Roll the chicken in the oil mixture to coat; arrange in the pan.
Sprinkle with the pieces of fresh basil.
Arrange the lemon slices around the edges of the chicken.
Bake 8 minutes.
Using tongs turn the chicken over. Place a lemon slice on each of the pieces of chicken.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer or until cooked through.
Serve warm or at room temperature with the pan juices spooned on top.

title: oven-baked apple slices(credit: julia childs)
directions: Quarter, core and peel the apples; cut the quarters into lengthwise slices.
Toss in a bowl with the sugar, then with the lemon juice and finally with the melted butter.
Let sit 3 or 4 minutes to render juices.
(Meanwhile, preheat oven to 425°.) Turn apples into baking dish and set in middle level of oven, basting every 8 to 10 minutes with juices.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until apples are tender.
Serve as is or with cream, custard sauce or vanilla ice cream.
Utterly delicious!

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Divide dough in half.
Use one-half for bottom crust.
Other half can be rolled out and cut into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Weave strips in a lattice pattern.
Crimp top and bottom edges together.

title: pineapple sour cream roll-ups
directions: Mix all together.
Divide dough into 8 balls.
Flatten, put on a plate and refrigerate.

title: no salt baked chicken
directions: In small bowl, mix together maple syrup, mustard, onion and curry powder.
Rub each chicken breast with garlic; arrange in baking pan.
Brush syrup-mustard sauce on chicken, then sprinkle with pepper.
Place chicken in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, turn chicken and brush with remaining syrup-mustard sauce.
Return chicken to oven and continue cooking until brown and crisp and fork can be inserted with ease, about 30 minutes more.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all together.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add molasses, sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook to hard crack stage, stirring constantly.
Quickly stir in coarsely chopped nuts.
Spread in lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool thoroughly; turn out onto waxed paper.
Spread top with melted chocolate and finely chopped nuts.
Chill; break into pieces.

title: orange roughy with red peppers
directions: For extra-crisp peppers when cooking this dish in the microwave, omit the step of cooking the peppers before adding the fish.
If fish fillets are large, cut into 4 serving pieces.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Layer onion and bell peppers in skillet; sprinkle with half of the thyme and half of the pepper.
Place fish over bell peppers and sprinkle with remaining thyme and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook until fish flakes easily with fork, 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan and bring to a boil the sugar, milk, margarine, cocoa, salt and vanilla.
Remove from heat and add the oatmeal, chopped nuts and shredded coconut. Stir well. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Makes 4 dozen.

title: squash and chicken casserole
directions: In
casserole
dish
melt margarine; toss with stuffing mix. Remove
stuffing mix from dish.
Pour squash and chicken mix in casserole
dish
and
top
with stuffing mix.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, or until light brown and casserole is bubbly.

title: patty pan squash in chive butter
directions: Put squash, salt and water in a 3-quart covered saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook approximately 3 minutes, until tender.
Pour off water.
Add butter and chives; simmer on low heat for 2 minutes.
Serve in heated dish.

title: chicken mandarin
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces.
Shake in a paper bag with flour to coat.
In a skillet, heat oil and margarine; add chicken and brown each piece.
Drain mandarin oranges and set aside.
Mix juice from the can with the lemon juice, orange juice, honey, shoyu and ginger.
Pour sauce over the chicken in skillet.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.
Add mandarin oranges 5 to 10 minutes before chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown onion in margarine; add bell pepper and cook until wilted.
Add corn, sugar and pimentos.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Beat 1 egg and add to corn mixture.
Mix with rice and put in shallow baking dish; top with American sliced cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: basic italian sauce
directions: Use hot skillet.
Put in olive oil.
Get hot again and add garlic and stir until it starts to turn color.
Quickly add onion to cool garlic and stir until onions are clear.
Add all spices and stir well so the spices are mixed in.
Add tomatoes and turn down to low heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add tomato paste within the hour and stir several times.
Remember to stir from the bottom of the skillet.
If your skillet isn't big enough you might want to use a bigger pan.
This is a low-fat and low cholesterol sauce, unless you add pepperoni or Italian sausage.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump in pineapple and cherry pie filling and spread over bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Sift cake mix evenly over fruit.
Sprinkle with pecans over cake and mix.
Cover with butter pats.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon angel squares
directions: Pour boiling water on Jell-O; stir until dissolved. Refrigerate until jelled but not set.
Add enough cold water to lemonade concentrate to measure 2 cups.
Stir into Jell-O; beat until foamy, fold in whipping cream.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugars, vanilla, syrup, soda and butter.
Add peanut butter.
Beat until blended.
Add oatmeal, M&M's and chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet with tablespoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until light brown; let stand 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sugar free applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray muffin pan cups with vegetable oil cooking spray. In medium size bowl stir together flour, oats, Splenda, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and cream of tartar. Set aside.

title: hungry man's baked beans
directions: In preheated pot, saute veggies.
Add beef and seasonings; cook until done, stirring occasionally.
Drain and set aside.
In same pot, add baked beans, brown sugar, hot sauce and season to taste.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add beef mixture; simmer 5 minutes more.
Pour baked bean mixture into baking dish; cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: insalata(italian tomato salad)
directions: Slice the tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese about 1/4 inch thick (use very sharp knife for tomatoes).
Alternate slices of each on a platter overlapping each layer.
Sprinkle with basil, olive oil and salt.
Serve with warm garlic bread.

title: "bark" (candy)
directions: Line flat
pan
with
1-inch
sides with aluminum foil, then spray with
Pam.
Layer bottom of pan with saltine crackers, placing salty side down.
Place margarine and brown sugar in small saucepan over medium heat, stirring, until melted and well blended.
Pour over crackers and spread to coat.
Preheat oven
to 400° and bake for 5 to 10 minutes until well heated. Take
pan out
of
oven
and sprinkle chocolate chips on top. Spread
with wooden
spoon while melting until evenly coated. Place in refrigerator and chill until hard.
Peel off aluminum foil and then break into pieces. Store in covered container.

title: sweet bread(no kneading required)
directions: In a large enamel or porcelain utensil, measure out the water and sprinkle yeast over top to soften.
Set it aside.

title: impossible garden pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomatoes, onions and cheese in pie pan.
Place remaining ingredients in blender and beat on high speed for 15 seconds (or 1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour into pie pan.
Bake about 30 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: heavenly hash browns
directions: Thaw potatoes until workable.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: swiss spinach quiche
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Add spinach, milk, eggs and seasoning; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rolls
directions: Warm the oil, milk and water all together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Butter pan and cook until brown in a 400° oven.

title: diabetic whoopie pies
directions: Mix cake mixes and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done and cool.
Mix diabetic frosting with peanut butter.
Fill cookies.

title: mama van's vegetable meatball soup
directions: *Mix meat, salt, pepper and garlic powder for taste.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with
the
juice
from can of fruit cocktail and 2 eggs.
Mix
until
smooth
and add fruit.
Pour into greased and floured
9 x 14-inch Pyrex pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup nuts over top and cook 45 minutes at 325°.

title: crunchy ham rolls
directions: Combine cream cheese, peanuts and garlic.
Spread each slice of ham with mixture; roll as for jelly roll.
Chill thoroughly; cut into slices.
Serve each slice on round cracker if desired. Yield:
48 servings.

title: cocktail ryes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on bread liberally.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350 degrees or until slightly bubbly and brown.
If baked too long bread will become dry and hard.

title: dinong's dinoldug
directions: Peel taro; cut	into
to 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Put into large pot.
Fill	with
water
to just cover taro.
Cook until gravy starts to
form.
Add
grated coconut and can of coconut milk. Add sugar to taste.

title: easy taco pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix. Prepare pizza crust according to package on 12-inch pizza pan or jelly roll pan.
Spread beef mixture over crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 19 minutes on bottom rack until crust is golden brown.
Top with lettuce, tomato and sour cream.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Combine bran, sugar, salt, soda and flour.
Add eggs, margarine and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in covered container (preferably glass) in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Use as desired or bake all at once and freeze.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes a lot.

title: strawberry rhubarb shortcake
directions: Hull and chop pint of strawberries.
With fork blend baking mix, milk, corn oil spread and sugar.
Spread into greased pan. Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes on wire rack.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Cook rhubarb and cornstarch with 1/2 cup sugar on medium heat stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in strawberries while rhubarb mixture is still hot.
Slice shortcake in half horizontally.
Place bottom half on cake plate.
Spoon strawberry mixture on top, then Cool Whip.
Replace top and garnish.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg white until stiff. Add brown sugar. Stir in 1 1/2 cups whole pecan until coated.
Drop by small spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Turn oven off and leave in oven for 40 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: This recipe will make 8 layers, 2 cakes.

title: shoo-fly bake
directions: Mix by hand the flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumbs.
Add ginger, cloves and cinnamon.
Dissolve soda in the warm water.
Add it to the mixture.
Add the molasses and beat until smooth.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix first 4 ingredients in a punch bowl. Add 7-Up or Sprite.
Add drops of red food coloring, if desired. Stir.
Float block of ice; garnish with fruit slices.
Makes 32 servings.

title: date bread
directions: Put shortening in hot water.
Add the soda and pour over chopped dates.
Mix and let stand while mixing dry ingredients. Mix all dry ingredients and add to the liquids, mixing well.
Add the nuts last.
Fill a well-greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about one hour and 10 minutes (or until well done).

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook pepper and onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Add rice, thyme, salt, pepper and bacon.

title: crab ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Add to warm soup.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in mold overnight.
Unmold on platter and serve with crackers, especially Wheat Thins.

title: grandma moore's oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla. Alternate adding dry ingredients and mashed bananas, mixing well. Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions until tender, drain and combine remaining ingredients and pour mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian penuche candy
directions: Mix pineapple, sugars and cream.
Boil until soft ball stage. Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Stir until cool.
Pour into a buttered pan and cut.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour, stir in broth.
Add soup, sherry and seasonings.
Divide in half.
Add spaghetti and mushrooms to half and place in buttered casserole dish.
Add turkey to remaining sauce and spread over top of spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "white palace" burgers
directions: Mix Underwood liverwurst spread, ground beef, onion powder, pepper and seasoned salt.
Shape in six (6) thin rectangular patties.
Fry patties and chopped onions on a lightly greased grill or skillet.
As patties fry, make holes in them here and there with the tip of a knife.
Serve on small "burger buns" with plenty of onions and a dill pickle chip.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients, press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix next 2 ingredients and spread over first layer.
Slice as many bananas lengthwise as desired and spread over second layer. Spread pineapple over third layer.
Spread Cool Whip over fourth layer and spread chopped pecans over fifth layer.
Keep refrigerated until serving time.

title: eggplant soup
directions: Saute celery, onion and green peppers in butter until tender and transparent.
Add eggplant and zucchini and cook until tender. Add tomatoes, chicken broth, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 1/2 hour or until all vegetables are tender. Serve plain or with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.

title: meringue topping for pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until makes soft peaks. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread on pie.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° until brown.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Mix, bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Trim all crust from cake, then cut cake into 1-inch cubes.
Put half of cake cubes into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with pie filling.
Add remaining cake cubes in a layer.

title: ham delights
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients together.
Slice rolls in half and put ham and cheese in them.
Put rolls back together and pour sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: veggie stew
directions: Heat oil on medium; 5 minutes later add onion.
Wait 2 minutes and add peppers.
Two minutes later add garlic, mixing at all times.
Stir in tomatoes and remaining vegetables.
Add dressing and mix well.
Cover and cook until veggies are all tender.

title: quick cocoa cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add all together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Great for cupcakes also.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat batter ingredients until very smooth.
Heat oil to 375°. Pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel, holding finger over opening. Swirl batter into hot oil by using a bull's eye circular pattern. Fry until brown, then turn with tongs.
Fry second side. Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve with hot maple syrup.

title: park city chili verde
directions: Lightly dredge the pork in flour, then brown lightly in olive oil in a large Dutch oven. Remove pork; lower the heat and cook the onion and garlic until quite fragrant.
