Return pork to the dish and add the canned chiles and tomatoes. If you like your chili really zesty, add some minced jalapenos or serranos too. Add additional liquid to almost cover the pork. Simmer covered until pork is just tender. Season with cumin and chili powder - be very generous with cumin as it is what really sets this chili apart. Three to four tablespoons is not unusual. Simmer about 30 minutes more and serve with heated tortillas and if you wish, some grated Jack cheese on top. This both reheats and doubles well. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, softened, and milk.
Add flaked crab meat, finely chopped onion, horseradish, salt, pepper and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve piping hot with crackers or small rye bread.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Start heating oven to moderate 350°.
Place these ingredients in layers in a 2-quart baking dish with a tight fitting lid:
first rice, then corn; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water and layer onion, green pepper and ground beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour second can tomato sauce and 1/4 can water.
Cover meat with bacon, cut in halves.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer until bacon is crisped.

title: hornberger's fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except, chocolate chips, in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly as it will scorch easily.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour in chocolate chips.
Mix well, (I use my electric mixer just to help blend).
Do not over mix.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order given in a 12 x 9-inch glass dish.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar; spread evenly over top of salad.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage get to room temperature. Mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick. Roll into balls. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Peel and cook potatoes; slice into casserole dish (7 1/2 x 10-inch).
Slice and layer apples on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine together.
Heat on stove top until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and cocoa to mixture.
Stir until well blended, then add the oats.
Drop onto wax paper and let the cookies set.

title: yellow rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package and cool.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over rotini.
Make a day ahead; stir frequently.

title: mexican mountain
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add all other ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes. Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese. Heat until cheese is melted. Garnish with lettuce, black olives, onions, sour cream and Doritos.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in saucepan.
Blend in milk and syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it boils. Boil one minute; remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Serve warm.
Great with yellow cake and vanilla ice cream.
Kids love this sauce over twinkies also.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot or Dutch oven.
Heat and serve.
Unusually good for such a quick and easy recipe!

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 4.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Sauce:
Spray Dutch oven with Pam.
Pour excess liquid off of canned tomatoes into pot.
Mince tomatoes in food processor.
Put in pot.
Add 4 cans tomato sauce and 4 cans water.
Chop onions and garlic in food processor.
Add to tomato mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add oregano, sugar, parsley and bay leaf.
Bring to bubbling heat, then reduce to a low simmer, stirring about every 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cook for about 3 hours.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: Saute onions, garlic, basil, oregano and bay leaf in oil, about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 2 tablespoons parsley to onion mixture.
Cook on low temperature for 1 hour; set aside.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Place all ingredients except champagne in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Chill.
Just before serving, stir in champagne. Garnish with additional sliced or whole strawberries.
Can be served as a beverage.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; drain.
Add tomato sauce. Pour in a greased casserole dish.
Drain green beans.
Top ground beef with beans.
Sprinkle onion rings over this.
Mix creamed potatoes according to directions on box.
Spread potatoes over and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin gooey butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into a lightly greased 13 X 9 inch baking pan.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Tear bread into small pieces and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown sausage, drain and sprinkle over bread crumbs.
Place grated cheese over sausage.
Beat 6 eggs, 2 cups of milk and mustard; add salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Bake at 350° for 35 to
40 minutes.
May prepare the night before and bake the next day.

title: tex-mex soup
directions: Combine water, broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and green pepper and bring to a boil.
Add chicken; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add corn, beans, cumin, chili powder and pepper.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes or longer.
Place crushed tortilla chips, grated cheese and diced avocado in a bowl and ladle soup over.

title: red lobster cheesy garlic rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop dough in heaping teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Combine melted butter and garlic. Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. This recipe, like basic black dress, is basic.
It may be useful for coffee cake, upside-down cake, cupcake, fruit cake, etc.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add jello to hot water and dissolve it.
Drain pineapple.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Stir well and chill.

title: lemon cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cake mix, egg and margarine in large bowl at medium speed until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Press evenly on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes. Cool completely.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture; beat smooth.
In deep skillet, heat oil to 360°.
Covering spout, pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Remove finger and release batter into oil in a spiral, starting in center and winding out.
Fry until golden, about 3 minutes.
Turn carefully; cook 1 minute longer.
Drain on paper toweling.
Dust with powdered sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 6 to 8 funnel cakes.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Cook down blackberries in 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water until sugar is melted.
Melt oleo in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour on top of oleo.
Then add blackberry mixture on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hearty chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts in 4 cups of water for 20 minutes or until done.
Debone and chop chicken.
Add chicken and all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: finnish carrot casserole
directions: Cook and mash carrots; cook rice until soft and mix with carrots.
Mix egg with milk and add to carrot mixture.
Season with salt.
Pour into greased casserole.
Dot with butter and bake in a 350° preheated oven for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: lemonade dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth. Serve with fruit salads.

title: pecan fudge nuggets
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Set aside and grease a cookie sheet.

title: nut and raisin spread
directions: Finely chop orange and nuts in food processor.
Add half of raisins and all of mayo.
Process until raisins are chopped.
Add remaining raisins.
Cover and process until chopped.
Store in refrigerator up to two weeks.

title: fresh peach or strawberry pie
directions: Have water boiling.
Mix sugar, jello and cornstarch together. Pour into boiling water.
Stir constantly until thick and shiny (about 5 to 7 minutes).
Remove from heat and add food coloring, butter and peaches.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: english pea salad
directions: Line bowl with lettuce.
Then put onion, celery, green pepper and peas in layers.
Tear rest of lettuce and use it as next layer.
Then add sugar, salad dressing and cheese.
Fry bacon and crumble over the top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: snow logs
directions: Cut banana the long way.
Put peanut butter on banana halves. Put the other half banana on top.
Roll banana logs in coconut. Put Snow Logs on wax paper and freeze slightly.
Serves 5.

title: burnt sugar coconut candy
directions: In a heavy skillet, burn sugar to a medium brown.
Add Karo syrup to sugar.
Add milk a little at a time (do not stop boiling process).
Cook to soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat and add soda. Stir quickly until foam goes down.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Beat very hard.
Pour into buttered dish to harden.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix fruit and other ingredients; let set 20 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter; put on top crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Place first three ingredients in pan and heat until well blended.
Set aside.
Mix 1/4 cup water and gelatine until blended. Add to soup mixture and let cool.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together with the soup mixture.
Place into mold and chill in refrigerator at least several hours.

title: baked shredded carrots
directions: Lightly toss together carrots and onion.
Put sugar and salt with mixture until combined.
Spread in 1-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: double duty salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cottage cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and use as a spread on crackers.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups spread.

title: party chicken
directions: Dip 10 to 12 pieces chicken in marinade made with ingredients. Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour leftover marinade over chicken pieces.
Marinate at least 8 to 10 hours. Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° until bubbly and well browned.
Serve with rice or noodles using pan sauce as gravy.
Enjoy!
Can be frozen.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
Delicious on crackers.

title: chicken with olives and tomatoes
directions: Mix 4 tablespoons olive oil, 2 garlic cloves, minced, lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste in shallow baking dish (large enough to hold cutlets in a single layer).
Add cutlets and turn to coat.

title: quick low-fat dinner for two(low cholesterol)
directions: Salt and pepper cutlets to taste; coat with margarine or Mollie McButter, mixed with small amount of water.
Sprinkle chives on top.
Place in shallow dish and bake at 325° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve with baked potatoes topped with nonfat sour cream and chives.
Add a garden salad with nonfat dressing.

title: tea time sandwiches
directions: Blend mayonnaise and Blue cheese with the cream cheese.
Add chopped nuts, salt and Worcestershire; mix well.
Spread on lightly buttered bread rounds.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: eggnog(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients except nutmeg in blender container. Blend about 30 seconds. Pour into cups and sprinkle with nutmeg. Serves 4.

title: aunt joyce's cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and almond extract.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool 20 minutes.
Beat sour cream, vanilla and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pour over cake and bake 10 minutes.
Remove and refrigerate.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Saute onion, celery and chicken separately in skillet with a small amount of oil.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add 3 to 4 eggs (depending on the amount to be served).
Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of mixture in skillet, forming patties.
Brown lightly on both sides.
To serve, place 2 to 3 patties on plate; cover with cooked rice and Basic Brown Sauce, with soy sauce, if desired.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: In a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer rice, ham, onion and broccoli.
In separate bowl, combine soup, cheese and milk.
Spread over broccoli.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, make coarse bread crumbs in a blender with bread slices.
Saute crumbs in butter over medium-high heat until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Continue baking 15 minutes longer or until hot and chunky.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onions, using grating disc or food processor or large holes of grater.
Put potatoes and onion in wire strainer and squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Transfer to bowl and mix in egg, salt, flour or Matzoh meal and baking powder.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Drop 2 tablespoons of mixture in pan.
Flatten with spoon and fry over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until brown.
Serve hot with sour cream or applesauce.

title: harvard beets
directions: Bring to boil.
Stir while cooking.
Add cubed beets which have already been cooked.
Allow to sit in warm place on stove for 1/2 hour.
Then add 2 tablespoons butter before serving.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice, milk and butter or margarine in a saucepan and cook on medium heat until steaming.
Turn to low and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

Beat eggs; add sugar and vanilla. Pour boiling rice mixture gradually into egg mixture and stir. Pour into buttered casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 325°. After 15 minutes, stir and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: First take oatmeal and boiling water.
Mix this and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Then cream together oleo and sugars.
Mix this with the oatmeal mixture.
Then add eggs, flour, salt, vanilla and soda.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Heat filling over stove or microwave.
Spoon 1/4 cup into center of flour tortilla.
Fold bottom over filling; fold in sides, then fold down on top to enclose filling completely.
Deep fat fry chimichangas, two at a time, turning once, in 1/2 inch of vegetable oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Top with salsa, shredded lettuce and sour cream as desired.

title: turkey and avocado sandwich
directions: Mix mustard and mayonnaise and spread on bread.
Layer turkey on bread, not flat, but wrinkled.
Repeat with Swiss, then avocado, tomato, lettuce and sprouts.
Bon Appetit!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar and oil, mixing well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine walnuts and raisins with 1 teaspoon flour. Stir into batter.
Pour into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into loaf cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot pepper pecans
directions: Melt butter in baking pan. Spread pecans evenly in pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Combine soy sauce, salt and Tabasco sauce. Toss with pecans. Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: hamburger mac
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package. Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients to meat, including macaroni and cheese dinner.
Mix.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: goblin guzzler
directions: Place 1 scoop (1/2 cup) vanilla ice cream in each of the four 10 ounce glasses.
Pour 1/2 cup Juicy Juice in each glass.
Slowly top each float with 1/4 cup sparkling water.
Serve immediately.

title: chilled filled cantaloupe
directions: Cut the melons into halves lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds and drain well.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Add banana.
Place melon halves in small bowls.
Spoon in gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut into wedges.
Garnish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bacon poles
directions: Cut bacon lengthwise (with scissors) in half, making 2 long thin strips from each slice.
Wrap one strip in a spiral around each bread stick.
Place double thickness of paper towels in bottom of 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Arrange so they don't touch each other.
Cover with paper towel.
Cook on High for 5 to 8 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn every 2 1/2 minutes until bacon is done.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Combine margarine, mustard, onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Slice rolls in half (do not separate rolls; sliced rolls will look like a slab of mini hamburger buns). Spread the mixture on the rolls.
Layer with cheese slices and ham slices.
Put top of rolls back on.
Return to the aluminum pan that rolls came in and cover with foil.
Heat to 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until hot.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix all together.
Press in a 9-inch pie tin.

title: russian cream salad
directions: In saucepan, stir in first 3 ingredients until dissolved. Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Triple this for a large crowd.
Put strawberries in middle and around.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a 2-quart clay flowerpot.

title: cheese cake
directions: Put cream cheese in bowl at room temperature.
Add sugar and 1 egg and mix well.
Add 1 egg and mix well.
Then add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool and add fruit topping of your choice.

title: quick quiche(serves 4)
directions: Make batter:
Combine butter, eggs, milk, flour and seasoning (use a fork to mix).
Pour batter into Pyrex baking dish. Sprinkle ham and cheese on top.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple with juice and dry powdery pudding. Top with nuts and cherries.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar.
Add flour and beat.
Add milk. Melt margarine and add corn, salt and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in liquid. Add cranberry sauce. Add all others when jello starts to jell.

title: cashew nut hot dish
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put into baking dish and sprinkle with Chinese noodles.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: To serve, mix 3 teaspoons to cup of boiling water.

title: picadillo(soup from the philippines)
directions: In medium saucepan heat oil.
Brown garlic in hot oil, add onions and tomatoes, saute until tomatoes are mushy.
Add ground beef and saute until brown.
Season with patis, salt, pepper, sugar and m.s.g.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add potatoes. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: springtime punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Stir in lemon, orange and pineapple juices. Refrigerate.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine cocktail sauce, mayonnaise, lemon juice and dill in a medium bowl. Add crab (or shrimp), celery and bell pepper. Toss lightly to coat.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: In a medium-size bowl, mix honey and peanut butter.
Add cocoa mix until well blended.
Stir in oats and rice cereal until well coated.
Shape into balls the size of golf balls.
Refrigerate 30 minutes before serving.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan; stir in water, chocolate and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in butter and vanilla.
Spread on cake while frosting is hot. Delicious.
Enough for two 8 or 9-inch layers.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top and sides if desired.

title: peppered steak
directions: Brown steak that has been cut in 1/4-inch strips in butter in a heavy skillet on medium heat.
Add onion soup mix and water. Simmer abut an hour.
Add peppers, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer.
Serve on rice.

title: texas pot roast
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 12 hours.

title: rebecca's chicken cheese rolls
directions: Boil the chicken breasts slowly until tender.
Debone and cut into bite size pieces.
To chicken, add sauteed onions, mushrooms, peppers and 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Heat soup and add 1 cup shredded cheese and milk.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add dressing.

title: red rice and sausage
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper. Thinly slice sausage and brown. Add rice and tomato sauce. Mix and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix cake mix with pudding, oil, eggs and sour cream together. Set aside.
Mix brown sugar with cinnamon.
Pour a small amount of batter into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle part of the sugar mixture evenly over the batter. Continue layering, ending with batter.
Any leftover sugar sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: blueberry or blackberry pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar into bowl.
Pour berries into mixture and stir until every berry is coated.
Proceed as with any berry pie. Cook until juice bubbles out of crust.

title: lemonade drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat smooth.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to butter mixture.
Alternately add half of lemonade concentrate.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by tablespoon about 1 1/2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Lightly brush warm cookies with remaining lemonade concentrate and sprinkle lightly with sugar.

title: aunt ann's salad dressing
directions: Add all ingredients.
Shake well and store in refrigerator.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer each of the ingredients in a very large bowl. Spread 1/4-inch of mayonnaise over top, sealing at sides.
Sprinkle sugar all over top of mayonnaise. Fry and crumble 4 bacon strips for top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken; place in a large casserole dish. Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt and pepper.
Dice onion over chicken.
Slice Velveeta cheese over chicken.
Sprinkle 1/2 bag crushed Doritos over cheese.
In a separate bowl mix cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel and chicken broth; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Then put the rest of Doritos on top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: sour cream for baked potatoes
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble.

title: "eatin with lia"
directions: In saucepan, bring to a boil red cooking wine, sweet basil, thyme and clove of garlic (chopped).
Add cream of mushroom soup to ingredients in baking dish.
Stir well.
Add meat.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 325°, basting every 20 minutes.
Meat will fall apart. Pour gravy over mashed potatoes.
Side dish is corn-on-the-cob. Serves 6 hungry folks well!

title: mud hen cake
directions: Beat all ingredients and add 1 1/2 cups self-rising flour. Press in lightly greased pan.

title: chum-chicken-ley
directions: Flatten chicken breast halves between two sheets of wax paper to 1/8-inch thickness.
Coat chicken with flour and lightly brown in a skillet, using 4 tablespoons butter.
Pam coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place chicken into it, slightly overlapping each piece.
While browning chicken, saute mushrooms in the remaining butter.
Sprinkle mushrooms evenly over chicken.
With drippings left over from browning chicken, add broth and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour sauce evenly over chicken and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle the Mozzarella and then the Parmesan cheeses over chicken and bake additional 5 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Rinse in cool water.
Mix all other ingredients together, except 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° in a Pyrex dish.
Remove from oven and sprinkle the 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Bake just until it melts good.

title: deer chili
directions: Brown ground deer with onion; mix in all ingredients.
Cook until bubbly.
Great served on rice with crackers.

title: aida's cream cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add vanilla and cream.
Add flour and baking powder.
Spread in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Add olive oil to a large, hot skillet and saute the onion, garlic and celery until soft. Add all of the rest of ingredients (except shrimp and bell pepper) and simmer for 45 minutes or as long as 1 1/2 hours. You may have to thin it now and then with a bit more wine or water. About 20 minutes before serving, add the bell pepper. Add the shrimp and simmer for 3 to 4 minutes or until warm. Remove bay leaves and serve with hot, fluffy rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently; cover and chill 8 to 10 hours.
Drain.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar by hand.
Add 1 egg at a time, and cream.
Add baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Use cookie dispenser or drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Press onto cookie sheet with bottom of glass that is dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: instant banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add sour cream.
Layer bananas, wafers and pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done, about 10 minutes.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients except cranberry sauce and nuts.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour in half of batter, add half of cranberries and half of nuts.
Add remaining batter, top with remaining cranberry sauce and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: In an 8-inch skillet, over low heat, melt butter; turn heat off and thoroughly stir in graham cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press crumb mixture with the back of a spoon over the bottom and 1 1/2 inches up the sides of an 8-inch springform pan; set aside.

title: romy's easy key lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and let thicken.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 hours until firm.

title: crabmeat puffs
directions: Combine ingredients; spread on English muffins.
Cut into quarters or smaller.
Can be frozen on cookie sheet.
Store in plastic bags.

title: 4 bean hot dish
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain off fat.
Fry hamburger and onions.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: edwards' ham chicken divan
directions: Butter a long casserole dish.
Partially cook broccoli and drain; place in buttered dish.
Pull chicken in slivers, removing from bones.
Place on top of broccoli.
Place ham on top of chicken.
Mix the soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and sage and spread over casserole.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: jocelyn's california salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions, then chill. Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill before serving.

title: garden casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in butter until crisp-tender. Add flour; cook 1
minute,
stirring.
Spoon
half
of
onion mixture into a lightly greased
x
9 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer half each of
potato slices, green beans and cheese over onion mixture. Repeat
layers
of onion mixture, potatoes and green beans.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions, using a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan with a deeper depth than 2-inches (disposable aluminum lasagna pans work well).
Remove from oven and begin preparing fudge sauce.

title: fried rice
directions: Stir-fry bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Scramble eggs. Add peas and carrots and meat.
Fry until meat is done.
Add cooked rice; stir.
Add soy sauce, salt, pepper, onion powder and garlic powder.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together ground beef, rice, egg, onion, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic in small amount of fat.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Cook noodles as directed on package.
Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Alternate layers of meat sauce, noodles and cheeses in baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch, beginning and ending with meat sauce. Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamed chili taco
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until hot.
Serve over Fritos chips.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix rice according to directions.
Melt butter in frying pan, then stir in flour.
Add milk and stir on medium heat until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, then mix well with the rice. Pour in greased dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add French fried onions or sliced almonds on top and bake 15 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together. Add milk and egg.

Take shortening and melt in an iron skillet. While skillet and shortening are hot, pour in corn bread mixture. Bake at 400° for approximately 25 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: company potatoes
directions: Make the Potato Buds according to package instructions, but leave out the butter.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the prepared Potato Buds.
Mix with mixer.
Spoon into casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: miracle biscuits
directions: Blend baking powder into flour.
Make a well in middle of dry ingredients and dump in Miracle Whip.
Stir in liquid until soft dough stage is reached.
Knead on floured surface for 5 minutes. Flatten dough to 1-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds and let stand 10 minutes before baking in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Melt butter and cook onions until transparent.
Add broth, potatoes, parsley, mustard, salt and pepper.
Cook on low until potatoes are tender.
Then put mixture in blender with raw cucumbers and puree.
Chill well before serving.
Then add cream. The mixture lasts well for a week in the refrigerator for small servings.

title: spicy grilled lamb
directions: Combine mustard, oil, wine, garlic, herbs and pepper.
Place lamb in shallow dish.
Spread lamb with mustard mixture.
Cover. Marinate 1 hour at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator. Grill over medium coals 50 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Turn frequently.
Do not overcook.

title: chili
directions: Spray large pot with Pam.
Brown meat and onions which have been chopped.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, water and tomato sauce. Simmer for one hour.
Add beans and simmer thirty minutes until beans are tender.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn and put in large pan that will go into oven. Cook butter, brown sugar and Karo to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Pour this over popped corn.
Stir to coat and place in 250° oven 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and let cool.
Break apart.

title: 4 layer salad
directions: 1st Layer:
2 cups flour, 1 cup nuts and 2 sticks whipped margarine.
Mix this and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken italian
directions: Mix egg, pepper and salt together.
Dip chicken into mixture. Roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in large skillet in 1/2 cup vegetable oil.
Remove chicken; drain on paper towel.
Place chicken in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together the ingredients except the soup.
Pat to 1 1/2-inch thickness in pan.
Let
stand a couple of hours or overnight.
Cut out; fry until light
brown
on
both
sides. Place
in
baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup over meat and bake for 1 hour.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Mix and pour over chicken pieces.
Cover and bake on normal for 25 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn after 12 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours (covered).
Cool and shred with fork.
Serve on steamed buns.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix together with mixer, blending well. Pour into baking dish and freeze.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Bring Crisco, butter, cocoa and water to a boil.
Cool and add to the flour and sugar.
Mix well for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, buttermilk, salt, soda and vanilla. Beat well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Put cherry pie filling in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with cake mix and melted butter.
Place in a 350° oven for approximately 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice 4 medium potatoes.
Arrange in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and onions.
Pour on milk and dot with butter.
Cover with glass lid or Handi-Wrap.
Microwave on High, 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
If necessary to reheat, cover and put on Reheat 3 to 4 minutes.

title: bloody marys
directions: In a large pitcher, combine all ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Pour into salt-rimmed glasses.
Serve each with a celery stick stirrer, if desired. Makes 16 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixer bowl, cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 9 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift flour into large mixing bowl.
Mix well with sugar, raisins, pecans, spices and salt.
In another bowl, mix eggs, oleo and oil.
Add to dry mixture.
Mix bananas and soda.
Add to egg and flour mixture.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Add sugar and spices to ground apples and let stand for 1 hour.
Blend oil and unbeaten egg into apple mix.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to apple mixture, stirring until blended. Bake in 1 large or 2 small loaf pans that have been well-greased. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow
Solomon's prescription in Proverbs 23:14 (beat). Observe what
10 women did in Leviticus 26:26 (bake in oven) at 350° until done, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Blend together cream cheese, Dream Whip and sugar, then add milk, vanilla and pie filling.
Put mixture into a graham cracker crumb crust and top with cherry pie filling.

title: coke-cola cake
directions: Mix in saucepan the margarine, oil, cocoa and cola. Bring to a boil, then mix with the sugar, buttermilk, eggs and flour. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: In a large bowl mix first 4 ingredients (pumpkin, brown sugar, vegetable oil and egg).
Whisk until smooth.
Sift together all dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Stir flour mixture into pumpkin mixture, adding small amounts at a time.

title: pastry puffs
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring water, butter and salt to boil. Add flour all at once; beat with a spoon until mixture forms a smooth ball and does not stick to pan.
Remove from the heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue to beat until dough is well blended and loses its shine.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet, making six mounds 3 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and dry and firm to the touch.
Cool on a wire rack. When completely cool, cut in half and gently remove any moist dough.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Stir in the bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown and firm. Makes 10 to 12 servings.
May also add onions, green pepper and ham, if desired.

title: saturday night casserole
directions: Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread each slice of bread with butter.
Arrange 3 to 4 slices of bread on bottom of casserole (trim to fit).
Cut remaining bread slices in half on diagonal.
Put 2 halves together sandwich fashion, butter inside. Stand sandwiches, spoke fashion, point up, around casserole. Place tomato slice between two sandwiches.

title: salmon croquette
directions: Place salmon liquid and all in bowl.
Remove bone and skin. Flake with fork.
Add beaten egg and cracker crumbs.
Add baking powder and flour.
Shape into small patties, roll in cornmeal and fry in hot oil or shortening.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot or cold.

title: layered green salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a deep dish in the order listed. Make at least 6 hours before serving (preferably one day ahead). Refrigerate.

title: triple bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except salad oil. Cover.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine, oil and marshmallows over medium heat until very smooth and creamy. In a LARGE bowl, pour mixture over popped popcorn and stir to coat. Then stir in peanuts and M&M's; mix until everything is coated and sticky. Press into a greased Bundt pan. (I spray it with Pam). Allow to set up. If you're in a hurry, an hour or two in the refrigerator does it. Otherwise, on the cabinet until it is cool will work. To turn out of the pan, first set the pan into 3 or 4-inches of hot water for a few seconds, then turn out onto a flat tray. I usually slice it with an electric knife. Does not require refrigeration.

title: artichoke pickles
directions: Make paste of flour, mustard, salt and 1 pint vinegar.
Heat 2 quarts vinegar, sugar and hot pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add flour paste.
Chop or dice vegetables and add.
Stir until vegetables are heated.
Do not boil.
Add turmeric.
Stir.
Put in jars.
Yield: 16 to 18 pints.

title: hummus
directions: Place garlic, parsley and onions in a food processor or blender and mince.
Add chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice and salt; puree to a thick paste.
Season to taste.
Transfer to a tightly lidded container and chill.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: pumpkin cake(serves 12)
directions: Beat well with fork until all is absorbed.

title: hash browns and sausage brunch
directions: Prepare hash browns according to package; stir in onion and parsley.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in flour, milk, salt and pepper until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and lift with fork.
Lay sausages on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be made the night before.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Gradually add vanilla and lemon flavor.
Beat one egg at a time.
Add flour, little at a time. Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and let set.
Top off with remaining ingredients.
Mix and frost.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Combine
ground
tomatoes and sugar; cook until bubbly. Remove from
heat	and
stir in Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Put in sterilized jars and keep in refrigerator.

title: pasta salad (1)
directions: Mix above and chill overnight.	Then add 1 chopped green or red pepper, 1 chopped onion, 1 tomato and 8 oz. shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in small amount of boiling, salted water until tender. Drain and mash.
Add margarine, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, milk, beaten egg and 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Mix well. Pour into buttered casserole. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Drain most of the juice off the sliced peaches.
Line the pie shell with peaches.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Into butter and sugar mixture, work in the flour.
Beat the egg into the mixture. Add the vanilla.
Spread mixture over top of pie and between peaches.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour, or until done.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in large skillet.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil. Add peanut butter and Krispies.
Press into pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together.
Spread on top.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Line baking
dish
with
beef.	Split,	debone and skin chicken breasts.
Wrap each piece with 1/2 slice bacon.
Place on top of beef.
Mix soup, sour cream and water or milk.
Pour over chicken. Bake in a 250° oven for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Mix first three ingredients.
Beat butter, peanut butter and brown sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until thoroughly blended. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheet.
With tines of fork, press down on each cookie to make a crisscross design.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Remove to a wire rack to cool.
Makes 50.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Press slightly with fork tines and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In microwave dish, put butter, Karo syrup and brown sugar. Microwave on High for 1 minute. Take out and stir. Microwave for another minute. Remove from microwave and stir. Add the baking soda and microwave 1 more minute.

title: cherry tomatoes
directions: Place a large non-stick skillet over a low heat and when it is hot, add the olive oil.
Add the garlic and cook until it just begins to turn golden, about 3 minutes.
Raise the heat to medium, add the tomatoes and cook them until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add the rosemary and cook about 1 minute.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles. Pat dough to cover bottom of large cookie sheet (greased).
Pinch seams together and crimp slightly around edges.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Allow crust to cool.
Combine softened cream cheese with dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread mixture over cooled crust.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables over top.
Use a variety of color for an attractive pizza.

title: coca-cola pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan. Mix catsup and Coke and pour over pork chops. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins for 5 minutes in water just covering raisins. Beat together cornstarch, sugar, eggs and salt.
Add to boiling raisins and cook until clear; about 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and cook 2 more minutes.
Let cool.
Make 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 400° about 50 minutes.
Let cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in any size pan.
Break up half into bottom of punch bowl.
Save the other half for top layer.
Spread strawberries over bottom layer.
Spread pineapple over strawberries.
Make up pudding as directed on box.
Spread over pineapple.
Next, spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle coconut.
Top with pecans and cherries.

title: shrimp stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine until golden brown; add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are pink; add flour, salt and pepper. Coat shrimp; add mushrooms, juice and all.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Add can of water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
If too thick, add a little water.
Stir in sour cream and serve over rice.

title: meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites until they peak.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold into mixture of Ritz crackers, baking powder and nuts.
Pour into pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. This is good served with Cool Whip alone; but I like to drain a can of fruit cocktail and put on top and then add Cool Whip.

title: carrie's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees until firm in center.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray.
Line with wax paper and spread out pecans and coconut over wax paper evenly.
Mix cake mix according to box directions and pour over pecans and coconut in pan.
Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese (cream cheese should be softened).
Pour this on top of cake mix before cooking. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until done.
Let cool about 25 minutes and remove from pan.
Peel off wax paper.

title: mustard chicken
directions: Melt butter, pepper, salt and mustard in a saucepan. Wash and dry chicken pieces.
Rub each piece in mustard mixture.
Place onto foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 450°.

title: chocolate walnut cake
directions: Measure flour, sugar, salt, coconut, butter and milk into mixing bowl.
Beat vigorously by hand or mixer (medium speed) for 2 minutes.
Stir in baking powder and baking soda.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly by hand or mixer (medium speed) 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 deep 9-inch layer pans which have been rubbed with Crisco or lined with heavy wax paper.

title: deep dark chocolate cookies
directions: In a large bowl beat butter, sugars and vanilla on medium speed about 2 or more minutes or until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to oleo mixture, beating just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes or until set.
Cool 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes four dozen.

title: california muffins
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water; cool.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add water and 1 egg, beating well.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given, beating well after each addition.
Store in refrigerator overnight or up to 6 weeks.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen muffins.

title: favorite casserole
directions: Combine butter and onion powder in skillet over low heat.
Stir in cereal until coated; set aside.
Combine soup with milk, salt and Tabasco sauce in bowl; blend well.
Stir in mushrooms, peas and potatoes.
Pour into 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: greens
directions: Wash and remove stems from greens.
Wash again to remove any grit.
(If large collards, cut into small pieces.)

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place contents of vegetable seasoning packet from stuffing mix and oleo in a bowl.
Add hot water.
Stir to partially melt oleo.
Add stuffing crumbs; stir gently to mix. Mix soup and milk in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in chicken, vegetable and thyme.
Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Melt cheeses together in double boiler.
Saute sausage and hamburger in skillet until brown and crumbly; drain well.

title: sherbet dessert
directions: Pour melted margarine in bottom of Pyrex dessert dish. Reserve 4 tablespoons of graham cracker crumbs and pour the rest over the melted butter.
Spread the softened sherbet over the crumbs and cover sherbet with the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle the reserved graham cracker crumbs over the Cool Whip.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Then cut in squares and serve.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Finely chop and saute onions.
Cook rice in chicken broth. Remove chicken from bone.
Add Ro-Tel and celery soup to sauteed onion; simmer until smooth.
Butter casserole dish and line with rice.
Pour Ro-Tel, celery soup and onion mixture over rice. Slice Velveeta and top casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed Doritos. Bake at 350° until cheese is well melted, about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with Mexican corn and cornbread.

title: chicken and biscuit casserole
directions: Heat
oven
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons oleo until tender.
Add sherry (water), broth, 1/4 cup flour, salt and seasonings.
Cook
minutes until thick.	Place chicken and vegetables	in 2 quart casserole.
Combine 3/4 cup flour, oats and baking powder.	Cut in remaining oleo until crumbly. Stir
in milk and egg white until moistened.
Drop 1/4 cupfuls onto chicken.
Bake 38 to 42 minutes until golden.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Parboil shells for about 10 minutes; drain.
Mix together Ricotta, Mozzarella, eggs, grated cheese and parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Stuff shells using a knife or teaspoon. Cover bottom of a baking dish with sauce.
Arrange shells in a single layer, cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quaker cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well; beat in eggs and vanilla. Combine remaining ingredients and stir into creamed mixture; beat well.
Shape into walnut-size balls; place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield: 5 to 6 dozen.

title: almond crescents
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and almonds.
Sift together and work in the flour and salt.
Chill the dough.
Roll with hands, pencil-thick.
Cut in 2 1/2 inch lengths.
Form into crescents on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until set-not brown. Cool on pan.
While slightly warm, carefully dip into the confectioners sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 14-16 minutes.
Makes:
5 dozen 2 1/2 inch cookies.

title: mock candy bars
directions: Melt chocolate in oven at 300°.
Bring the syrup and sugars to a boil, stirring.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in the peanut butter, and then add the peanuts and corn flakes.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover with the melted chocolate.
Cool and cut into small bars.

title: pineapple cheese tarts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter 6 (5 ounce) custard cups.
Measure and set aside 1 tablespoon of the graham wafer crumbs.
Combine remaining crumbs with butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Press about 2 tablespoons of this mixture firmly against bottom and sides of each custard cup with a spoon.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in egg yolk, 5 tablespoons sugar, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and nutmeg.
Stir in pineapple.
Beat egg white until stiff and fold into pineapple mixture.
Spoon equal amounts of mixtures.
Set cups on a shallow pan and bake 20 minutes.

title: carrot pie
directions: In large bowl, mix well all ingredients except pie shell and cream. Pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated 375° oven 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Serve with cream.

title: creamy tarragon dip
directions: In blender at low speed or in food processor with knife blade attached, blend first 8 ingredients until smooth.
Pour mixture into small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with carrot sticks; Chinese pea pods, romaine lettuce leaves, cauliflowerets and/or zucchini slices.
If dip becomes too thick, upon refrigeration, stir in a little milk until it reaches dipping consistency.
Contains 50 calories per tablespoon.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples in a greased, shallow 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour water over apples.
In medium bowl, stir together sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon and salt.
Add butter. Using fingers, work in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle crumb mixture evenly over apples.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, until apples are fork-tender and topping is lightly browned.

title: pasta suzanne
directions: Saute chicken, bell peppers and onion in oil and butter.
Add cream, half and half, parsley and cheese and reduce heat.
Toss with cooked fettucine.
Garnish with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all together. Makes 3 layers.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit bars
directions: Mix the first first four ingredients together, then fold in Cool Whip topping.
Pour into a pan and freeze.
Cut into squares.

title: potato latkes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
(Grating some of your own skin adds unique flavor, but the use of a Cuisinart has been declared kosher.)
Lightly drain excess liquid.
Squeeze in garlic. Add egg, pinch of nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Add about 4 ounces of flour (to thicken to pancake consistency) and pinch of baking powder.

title: saucy meatball supper
directions: Combine beef, onion, eggs, milk, salt, pepper, bread, parsley and oregano.
Mix well.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Brown meat, then drain excess fat. Combine cheese soup, water and wine.
Add to meat in the skillet. Cook, covered, over low heat 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, salt, corn, milk and butter. Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy. Add oil and beat until well blended.
In a separate bowl, sift flour and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture. Beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, zucchini, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour. Cool 30 minutes.

title: black bean salsa
directions: In a food processor or blender, roughly chop the beans.
Be careful not to puree them.
Stir in the salsa, cilantro, cumin and lime juice.
Refrigerate overnight or serve immediately.
Serve with blue corn chips or an assortment of sliced vegetables such as zucchini, yellow squash and celery.
Makes 3 cups.
Calories:
15 per tablespoon.
Fat:
Cholesterol:

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Preheat frying pan to 350°.
Heat oil.
Dice onions in pan until brown.
Mix chopped meat with garlic, onion, salt, 1 egg and lots of bread crumbs.
Make meatballs and brown with onions.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix in shrimp. Marinate at room temperature for 1 hour or in refrigerator for 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
Prepare barbecue to medium-high. Thread shrimp on skewers.
Grill until just opaque, about 2 minutes per side.
Arrange skewers on platter.

title: virginia's skillet noodle candy
directions: Melt butterscotch bits, using warm heat.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Mix well; drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: goulash
directions: Cook meat and onion until done; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and 16 ounce can of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni; cook about 7 to 10 minutes.
Stir frequently until macaroni is done.
Add corn and heat through.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: In an 8 x 13-inch baking dish, put cream of chicken soup with just enough water to spread.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs.

title: chicken fried steaks and milk gravy
directions: Season meat with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Mix flour with 1 teaspoon pepper in shallow plate.
Dredge each steak in flour.
Dip in beaten egg, then dredge in flour again. Heat lard or oil in large, heavy skillet until hot.
Fry steak 3 to 4 minutes on each side, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the oil.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the dredging flour into oil.
Cook over medium heat 1 minute, scraping up browned bits from bottom of skillet.
Stir in milk, a little at a time, until gravy is smooth.
Cook, stirring frequently, 3 to 4 minutes, until thickened and bubbly.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 teaspoon salt; gravy should be quite peppery.
Serve steaks smothered in gravy.

title: frances may's chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl in order as given.
Mix well.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish and marinate for at least 1 hour, covered, in the refrigerator.
Stir occasionally.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix ingredients, except walnuts.
Grease a cookie sheet and then put waxed paper on it.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup finely chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (not any longer).

title: molasses crinkles cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip tops into sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lucky if you get any
directions: Mix flour, soft butter, sugar and nuts all together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix together the soft cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add the Cool Whip.
Mix and spread over crust.
Beat the instant pudding and milk until thick.
Chopped pecans can be added to this.
Spread this over cream cheese mixture.
Top with rest of 8 ounce Cool Whip.
Top with more nuts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together until fluffy.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet; flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until light brown on edges.
You may frost lightly, if you like.

title: clam chowder
directions: Chop the bacon and onion into bite size pieces.
Put chopped bacon pieces in skillet; saute and remove from skillet.
Blot grease from bacon with paper towel.
Add chopped onion to bacon grease and cook onion until translucent.
Blot grease from onion. Peel potatoes and cut into cubes.
Put bacon, onion and potatoes in a large crock-pot.
Add 3 cups water to bacon, onion and potatoes. Cook on high 3 hours.
Add the drained minced clams and milk. Continue to cook 2 more hours on low setting.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini (nut) bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat together sugar, zucchini and egg.
Add oil and lemon peel (or juice); mix well.
Combine flour mixture with zucchini mixture. Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes and then remove from pan. Cool.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients, one at a time, in order, beating well. Pour batter into a large, greased skillet or muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown (about 30 minutes).
Yield:
1 loaf or 12 muffins.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix and refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt and pepper.
When chicken is tender, remove from broth.
Tear chicken in small pieces; set aside.
Add milk to broth; bring to a boil.
Add uncooked noodles; cook until noodles are tender and broth is thick.
Add chicken pieces.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a slow cooker.
Simmer for 2 hours. Serve hot.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a pan, cook broccoli according to directions on bag. Drain and cut up in small pieces; set aside. Combine all other ingredients and mix well. Cook until onion is tender and add broccoli. Simmer until thick.

title: wagon wheel big chocolate cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl the flour, sugar and salt.
Put in pan and boil.
Pour over flour mixture and mix the water, oleo, Crisco and cocoa.
Cut into this mixture the eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 11 x 7-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine flour, sugar and pineapple (juice included) in top of double boiler.
Cook until thickened.
Add oleo; stir and let cool.
Peel and cut up apples.
Combine with cooled pineapple mixture.
Pour in bowl.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cherries are optional.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Spread cleaned wings in baking pan.
Spread 1/2 mixed sauce over wings.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Brush remaining sauce and cook 20 minutes longer.

title: shrimp with spinach soup
directions: Heat butter in a 4-quart saucepan on high heat.
Add garlic and shrimp.
Saute for a few seconds.
Add half of chicken broth, salt, white pepper and m.s.g.
Bring it to simmer.
Add spinach and cook for 2 minutes.
Add remaining chicken stock, stir and cover.
Simmer until spinach is soft.
Serve immediately.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread almonds on cookie sheet and bake until brown (10 minutes).
Cool completely.
Finely chop almonds into fine powder.
Set aside.
In mixing bowl, cream together softened butter and sugar.
Add egg and extracts.
Beat until blended with electric mixer on low speed.
Gradually add flour, salt and nuts until blended.
Transfer mixture to pastry bag or cookie press and form rosettes or stars.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: refrigerator cookie dough
directions: Melt butter and pour over brown sugar.
Add egg and mix well. Sift flour, soda and salt to mixture and add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Roll dough
in waxed paper to form a roll and place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken au gratin casserole
directions: Place beans and chicken in casserole.
Mix soup and water. Bring to a boil and pour over chicken.
Season to taste.
Combine bread, butter and cheese.
Toss lightly and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: anise cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out cookies.
Bake and let cool.
Make anise flavor icing and frost the tops of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then mix the rest of the ingredients together with dry mixture until well blended.
Bake in a 350° oven until well done, about 1 hour.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Press into this 1 cup of pecans. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over preceding. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain liquid.
Chop onion and fry with sausage.
Place a layer of squash, a layer of sausage and onion and a layer of yellow or Jack cheese until casserole dish is full.
Beat 2 eggs well and pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° until eggs are well done.

title: wallpaper cleaner
directions: Stir soda into flour; add ammonia and water.
Beat until smooth, then steam
in
double
boiler 1 1/2 hours.
Leave dough covered.
When cool enough to handle, knead it until smooth and soft.

title: white chicken chili
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender. Add chicken broth and chicken.
Simmer about 15 minutes until pink is gone from chicken.
Remove chicken; cool slightly and coarsely chop; return to saucepan.
Add chilies, corn, beans, jalapenos and herbs.
Simmer 15 minutes for flavors to blend.
To serve, place cheese in each bowl and add chili.
Garnish with chips, tomatoes and cilantro.

title: chicken adobos
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for the chicken.
Blend thoroughly.
Marinate chicken in sauce for 30 minutes.
Pour into electric frypan.
Cover; simmer until tender, approximately 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips. In skillet, brown meat and onion in butter. Sprinkle with salt, paprika and pepper. Add mushroom soup. Cover. Cook over low heat about 1 hour or until meat is tender. Stir now and then. Blend in sour cream just before serving. Serve over noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Dissolve yeast in water and add buttermilk.
Then add buttermilk and yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Mix; knead a few minutes.
Let stand 1 hour in greased bowl.
Punch down and roll out 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cover and let stand while oven preheats to 400°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Store dough in tightly covered container and refrigerate.
Can use up to 2 weeks later.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a
x 12-inch baking pan. Add ingredients by layers in order
listed.
Bake
at
325° about 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan, then cut into small squares.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under running water to thaw.
Drain thoroughly. Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese, chicken and onion in pie plate.
Beat milk, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake until it is melted, 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling, salted water for 6 or 7 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Gradually stir milk into soup.
Blend in egg.
Add eggplant, onion and stuffing; toss lightly.
Turn into greased casserole (about 1 1/2 to 2-quarts).
Bake at 350° until bubbly or hot through, about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with Cheese Topper.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Mix tuna and cream cheese till blended well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cut crescent triangles in half and put some of the mixture inside.
Bring triangle points together and pinch closed. Bake 350° for 20 minutes till golden.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook stew beef in large pot until fall apart tender.
Add cubed potatoes to beef and beef broth (add more water if needed) and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add vegetables, whole tomatoes, cabbage, V-8 juice and spices.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve hot with warm dinner rolls, cornbread or crackers.
Enjoy.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake the cake mix per directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use a large bowl or punch bowl.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in ovenproof bowl. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers or cocktail bread.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all together in a bowl; make into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: all american apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a 9-inch deep dish pie plate with vegetable spray.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, flour, lemon zest, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add apples to sugar mix. Stir until coated. Stir in raisins.
Spoon into prepared plate.
Place pie crust on top of filling. Trim edges, pressing against edge of pan.
Using a sharp knife, cut steam vents in pie crust. To glaze, lightly brush pie crust with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until pie crust is golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes. Cool on rack for 30 minutes.

title: four cheese chicken soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat. Add chicken, onion and garlic. Cook for 5 to 7 minutes or until onion and chicken are tender. In small bowl, whisk together milk and flour. Add milk mixture and broth to saucepan. Cook, stirring frequently, until thickened, about 10 minutes. Gradually stir in cheeses. Continue stirring until all cheeses are melted. Makes 4 servings.

title: toffee
directions: Line 9 x 13 pan with foil.
Lay saltine crackers in bottom of pan, salt side up.
(Do not overlap crackers.)
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar.
Continue stirring and bring mixture to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Continue stirring.
After 3 minutes, pour sugar mix over crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven.
Dump chocolate chips over pan.
Wait about 5 minutes, then spread chips.
Allow to totally cool, then break apart.

title: lisa's meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into balls 1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter.
Brown in small amount of shortening in skillet.
Cover with gravy and bring to a boil; simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spicy fruit
directions: Drain fruit and reserve 1/2 cup syrup.
Combine this syrup and add vinegar, cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add fruit and simmer 15 minutes, turning fruit occasionally.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave broccoli 5 minutes each package on High.
Add cheese and microwave on Medium for 2 1/2 minutes.
Saute onions in butter (microwave on Medium for 2 1/2 minutes).
Add soup and onions. Add stuffing mix (made by directions on package).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cereal snack
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients until melted and blend together. Bake at 225° for 40 minutes or 5 to 6 minutes in microwave.
Stir every 2 minutes.

title: corn 'n broccoli dish
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to blend.
Cover; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until crisply tender (8 to 10 minutes).

title: cheese pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat well.
Add Cool Whip.
Place into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
Chill and top with cherry or strawberry pie filling.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together. Heat each tortilla in microwave about 20 seconds. Spread on 1/8 of filling and roll up. Place seam side down in greased 12 x 8 inch dish. Pour sauce over rolls. Cover dish and microwave at high for 12 minutes. Cover with cheddar cheese. Microwave at high for another 1 to 2 minutes. Serve with sour cream garnish.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Soak bread in buttermilk for a few minutes.
Beat with beater. Add the eggs (beaten), then flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Mix well with egg whip.
Add butter or margarine and mix. Cook on a lightly greased griddle.
If pancakes are wet inside, add a little more baking powder and a little more flour.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and oranges with liquid and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake in 4 layers in 9-inch pans for 15 to 18 minutes, or 3 layers, but bake a little longer.
Let cool.
Ice.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in big pan.
When clear, add garlic salt, basil leaves, parsley flakes and oregano.
Fill pan with 1 quart cold water.
Leave 4 inches from top of pan.
Put raw diced potatoes in.
Cook at medium heat until soft (about 1/2 hour). Then blend 3 cups of soup and put back in pot.
Add milk, some potato mix and some grated cheese.

title: broccoli dip
directions: *You can use 1/2 pound Velveeta plus 1 tube Kraft garlic plus 1 tube Kraft jalapeno or 4 cans nacho cheese soup.

title: chicken and vegetables(serves 1)
directions: Boil chicken.
Coat wok with vegetable cooking spray and heat. Dissolve chicken soup in water; pour into pan.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients.
Serve when chicken is hot.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into mold and chill.

title: white cake
directions: Stir flour, sugar and shortening together.
Add milk and flavoring.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add unbeaten egg whites and continue beating 2 more minutes.
Batter will be thin. Bake in 2 (8-inch) greased and floured pans in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice with favorite icing.

title: black-eyed chicken salad
directions: Drain peas; add all ingredients and gently blend in mayonnaise and salt.
Serve on lettuce cup.
Great for leftover turkey.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer in order given.
Melt 2 sticks oleo and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter or margarine and 1 egg.
Press over bottom of rectangular cake pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook until thick all ingredients but coconut, then add coconut.
Pour in baked pie shells.
Top with meringue.
Brown in oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add broccoli frozen.
Stir until sauteed, then add remaining ingredients.
Place into a greased casserole dish.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wacky popcorn balls
directions: Place popcorn in a large, lightly buttered bowl.
Bring syrup, sugar and Kool-Aid mix to a boil in a saucepan.
Boil over medium heat until mixture separates into a hard thread when dropped into very cold water, about 6 to 7 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: In greased 10 x
x
3/4-inch
baking
dish,
combine croutons and cheese and
place
in
dish.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, mustard, onion powder and pepper.
Mix until blended and pour over crouton mixture.
Cook
bacon until crisp and sprinkle over top.
Bake in 325° oven for 55 or 60 minutes or until eggs are set.
Serves 6.

title: beef and snowpeas
directions: Marinate steak in 1 tablespoon oil plus the soy sauce and wine. Slice steak into 1/4-inch strips.
Save marinade.
Slice mushrooms and onions.

title: cheese strata
directions: Arrange alternate layers of bread, onion and cheese in shallow 2-quart baking dish, ending with cheese layer.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Set in shallow pan of water and bake for 25 minutes until bread is puffy and custard is set. Serves 4.

title: kristen's peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk, peanut butter, lemon juice and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Fill pie shell; dribble with chocolate syrup.

title: the mcwilliams italian artichokes
directions: Cut off stems of artichokes.
Cut about 1-inch off top and trim each leaf with scissors.
Spread open and wash thoroughly. Drain.
Mix all other ingredients except oil and fill artichokes with mixture, being careful to put some stuffing in all the leaves.
Set in deep pot with lid and add water to come halfway up sides of artichokes.
Pour 1 tablespoon oil over each.
Bring to boil, then simmer, covered, 1 hour or until tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal apple crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Put half on bottom; press.
Put rest of oatmeal mix on top of fruit and pat down.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; bring to boil, then cool. Add the flour and sugar. Beat in the eggs, sour cream and soda. Spread in greased and floured 12 x 15-inch jelly pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes, until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Prepare icing immediately; spread on cake while warm.

title: thanksgiving kuchen(or dyk filler, as lou calls it)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil, pumpkin and remainder of ingredients; mix thoroughly. Lightly oil and flour a tube pan so batter will not stick.
Add batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 10 minutes. Drizzle with orange frosting after cake is baked and cooled.
I prefer cake plain or with powdered sugar.

title: gourmet chicken in a hurry
directions: Mix.
Pour over raw cut up chicken pieces (2 to 3 pounds) in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans.
In a bowl, stir together the first 5 ingredients.
Set aside.

In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat next 4 ingredients until well blended. Gradually beat in flour mixture until well mixed. With spoon, stir in carrots and walnuts. Turn into prepared pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove and cool.
Fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: bocchara rice
directions: Soak rice in hot water for 1/2 hour minimum.
Mix spices and salt with tomato puree.
Fry onions until tender; add meat (on low heat). Keep on stirring until lightly browned.
Add tomato mixture and 1 cup water.
Cover and simmer over low heat.
Check if the meat or chicken are cooked, by sticking a fork in them. Boil the carrots in a separate pan adding salt to the water.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Drain carrots and add it to the meat mixture, then add the chickpeas.
Drain rice; add it to the meat along with 2 cups of water.
When the water boils, put it on low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve as a main dish with fine chopped tomato salad.

title: pancakes
directions: Turn mixer on start at top and add ingredients.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pancakes should be at least 1/2-inch thick.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in the water; add about 1 teaspoon salt. Cook until tender, about 30 to 45 minutes. Cool. Remove from bones and set aside. Strain broth.

title: crisp lemon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and blend well. Form into 1-inch balls, pressing firmly.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown around edges.	Cool 1 minute and remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies (strawberry cake mix may also be used).

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables until tender, drain.
Cook diced potatoes in chicken broth until tender.
Add soup and vegetables, cubed cheese and add to soup mixture.
Heat but do not boil.

title: party chicken
