directions: You will also need a 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion in a small amount of melted shortening.
Stir in salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Mix green beans and tomato soup into beef mixture.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mash potatoes, mix egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Spread mashed potatoes over ground beef mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pasta pot
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Combine everything, except cheeses, sour cream and shells.
Cook and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray tube pan with Pam.
Mix
sugar
with
teaspoons cinnamon.
Cut 2 cans biscuits
into quarters and roll in sugar mixture.
Put in tube pan and
pour some melted butter over it. Add 1 teaspoon of cinnamon
to
mixture and quarter another can of biscuits.
Roll in sugar and
add
to tube pan.
Add another teaspoon of cinnamon
to sugar
mixture.
Quarter
last
can of biscuits and do as before.
Pour
remaining
sugar and cinnamon over top.
Also pour rest of
butter
over top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Do not
slice,
just
pull
off
pieces and enjoy.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together, adding alternately with milk, to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° in three 9-inch cake pans.

title: summer squash bake
directions: Cook onions and squash in boiling water 5 minutes, then drain. In a bowl, combine soup, sour cream and stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onion mixture.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed croutons.
Spread half of croutons mix at bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole; spoon in mixture, then cover with remaining crouton mix.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: unleavened bread
directions: Blend honey, oil and milk together in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, wheat germ (optional) and salt.
Knead lightly.
Roll out thinly on a floured surface.
Roll dough over rolling pin to pick it up and transfer it to a cookie sheet.
Prick with a fork and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: blackened fish
directions: Combine in small bowl the paprika, salt, onion powder, garlic powder, black pepper, cayenne pepper, thyme and oregano.
This seafood seasoning mix will keep covered for weeks.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Arrange peach slices in pie shell.
In medium bowl, whisk together flour, 1/2 c. sugar, salt, and sour cream.
Spoon mixture over top of peaches.
Combine cinnamon and remaining sugar.
Sprinkle over pie.
Bake 30-40 minutes, until crust is browned and sour cream mixture is set.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream first 6 ingredients together. Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
May double recipe for 2 loaves.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, egg yolks, corn and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 375° until set and browned.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt on waxed paper or in small bowl.
Beat butter and sugar in large bowl until very light and creamy and beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour until combined (by hand or mixer).
Chill in balls (divide in half) for 2 to 3 hours.

title: hand-me-down chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch baking pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out dough; do not separate.
Pat flat in a pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pat's fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, eggs and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add fruit and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy pudding pie
directions: Mix together pudding and milk. Whip well, then fold in Cool Whip. Pour into a graham cracker pie shell. Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate torte
directions: In heavy saucepan, heat chocolate, butter and water over medium heat, stirring until blended.
Cool slightly.
Add egg yolks, sugar and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Chill until mixture is of spreading consistency, about 45 minutes.

title: basic "quick" mix
directions: Mix flour and powdered milk.
Add baking powder and salt; mix well.
Cut in shortening until it looks like small peas.
Store in airtight container.
Use as Bisquick.
Makes 9 cups.

title: spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add beaten eggs to flour and beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour evenly into shell. Bake for
1 hour.

title: nancy's butterscotch things
directions: Melt morsels. Add peanuts and noodles; stir. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper and let harden. (Can also be made with milk chocolate.)

title: bacon quiche biscuit cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, milk and eggs on low speed until smooth.
Stir in Swiss cheese and green onions.
Set aside.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Pat each biscuit into a 5 inch circle.
Place 1 biscuit in each greased muffin cup.
Firmly press in batter and up the sides, forming 1/4 inch rim.
Place half of bacon in bottom of dough lined muffin cups.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of the cheese mixture over the bacon in each muffin cup.
Place in oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until filling and edges of biscuits are golden brown. Remove from pan.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Wash and clean broccoli, then cut up.
Combine broccoli in medium pan with
onion,
thyme and chicken broth.
Bring to boil, until broccoli
is
soft.
Remove from stove.
Reserve a cup of the broccoli for later use.
Transfer remaining broccoli mixture to blender.
Whirl until pureed.

title: sloppy joes under a "bun"
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef in skillet until brown; drain. Stir in Sloppy Joes sauce. Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir baking mix, milk and eggs until blended.
Pour over beef mixture. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake 25 to 27 minutes
(if using Bisquick reduced fat baking mix, bake 28 to 30 minutes), or until crust is light golden brown.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter and blend with flour to make smooth mixture.
Add milk slowly and cook over very low heat, stirring constantly until thickens. Cook 3 to 5 minutes longer. Add cheese. Stir until cheese is melted. Be careful not to overcook.

title: veal marsala
directions: In a hot frying or saute pan, melt the butter and oil until hot (do not burn).
Dip veal, one piece at a time, in flour and place in hot pan.
Saute each side until lightly browned (do not overcook).
Remove from pan onto a platter until all pieces are done.
Keeping the pan on high heat, toss in the sliced mushrooms. Cook until mushrooms start oozing their own juices.
Sprinkle a tablespoon of flour over them and stir and cook a few minutes. Pour the chicken broth to deglaze the pan.
Return the veal pieces to the pan with the mushrooms.
Add salt, pepper and Marsala wine. Keep on high heat and watch the juices thicken.
This will only take a minute or two.

title: welsh rarebit (with beer)
directions: Melt margarine in pot.
Stir in flour, mixed with salt, pepper, cayenne and dry mustard.
Stir until smooth; remove from heat.
Add gradually the milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Stir.
Add beer until blended.
Add cheese.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Will keep hot over double boiler, stirring occasionally to prevent skin from forming.
Wire whisk very good for keeping mixture smooth.
Serve over toast or crackers.
Garnish with sliced tomato, bacon strips.
Serves 4.

title: pork chops - scalloped potatoes
directions: Take 1 side of beef or pork ribs, spread Barbecue Rub over ribs. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Prepare grill with charcoal and pecan wood. Place side of ribs on grill (NOT DIRECTLY OVER FIRE). Let smoke for 1 1/2 hours. Take off of grill; wrap in aluminum foil. Place back on grill for 2 to 3 hours longer. Internal temperature should be 160° to 170°.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat off. Place all ingredients in pot (or crock-pot) and cook.
(Stove top 1 1/2 hours on medium heat; crock-pot 3 to 4 hours.)

title: dirt cake
directions: Spread layer of crushed cookies in 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat cream cheese; add sugar, pudding mix and milk. Beat well. Spread layer of pudding mix over cookies. Add a thin layer of Cool Whip, layer of cookies, pudding and then Cool Whip until used up. Top with a thin layer of Cool Whip with a few cookies on top.

title: nancy's fudge
directions: Chill buttered platters before you make the fudge.
In a large saucepan, mix marshmallows, evaporated milk and sugar.
Boil on medium-high temperature for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, nuts, butter and vanilla.
Pour on buttered, chilled platter and chill.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with apple wedges.

title: carrot pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill.
Fold in other ingredients.
Put in refrigerator.
Ready to serve when firm.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish; salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Good served with rice.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix by hand.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll in sticks and chill until firm.
Slice and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
For dips.

title: grape macaroon salad
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Chill until thickened.	Blend in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: hungarian cheese
directions: Soften cheese and mix all well.
Divide into 6 balls.
Roll each into log and roll in chili powder.
Wrap and put into freezer.

title: arroz con dulce(rice pudding)
directions: Place rice in a saucepan with water to cover and let stand at room temperature for at least 5 hours or preferably overnight.

title: round steak italiano
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Coat with salt, oregano and pepper.
Place in crock-pot and pour spaghetti sauce over meat.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or until meat is tender.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine buttermilk and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle chicken with flour and seasoning, then dip into buttermilk mixture, coating both sides and using the entire mixture.
On sheet of wax paper, dip chicken into bread crumbs turning to coat on both sides with crumbs.
In small nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken and cook, turning one time, until browned on both sides.

title: old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Place meat and water in a large soup pot.
Bring to a boil. Skim surface occasionally.
When broth is clear, add tomatoes or juice, celery, onions and parsley.
Cover and simmer gently for 2 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, rutabaga and potatoes; simmer 1/2 hour. Remove soup bones from pot and cut meat from bones.
Return all to kettle.
Add peas, green beans and cabbage.
Season to taste. Simmer another 1/2 hour or until all vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cream together butter, shortening and sugar until real light.
Add vanilla and add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Beat well after each addition. Turn into tube pan, well-greased. Start off in cold oven.
Turn heat to 325° and bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Mix all above ingredients then pour over cooked meatballs. Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Crush graham crackers by hand or in food processor.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator for approximately 2 hours.
Shape into balls.

title: egg salad
directions: Mix together in pan eggs, flour, butter, vinegar and sugar; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Add evaporated milk and put in chopped onion.
Add cut up eggs and mix.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and coconut in electric blender container.
Cover and blend at low speed for 30 seconds. Fold mixture into whipped topping.
Spoon into crust; garnish with toasted coconut.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix as named and bake.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add salad oil, vanilla, carrots and eggs.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in raisins, coconut and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan and cool on rack.
Do not slice until bread has cooled completely.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: tuna swirls
directions: Mix oil and 1/2 cup milk together.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir with fork until it cleans sides of bowl.
Roll between sheets of wax paper into an oblong shape, 1/4-inch thick.
Mix tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Spread filling over dough.
Roll up beginning with wide side.
Seal by pinching edges.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.
Serve with a cheese sauce.

title: strawberry yogurt salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth, then add remaining ingredients.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Combine flour and salt. Dip eggplant slices into egg, then flour mixture.
Brown eggplant, half at a time, in hot oil for 3 minutes per side. Drain on paper towels.
Using the 1/2 eggplant, place in a single layer in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 the Parmesan cheese.
Top with half the sauce and half the Mozzarella cheese. Cut remaining Mozzarella cheese into triangles.
Repeat layers, last layer being Mozzarella triangles.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 400° or until hot. Serves 6.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions; cool.
Drain and save liquid from marinated artichoke hearts.
Add liquid to mayonnaise and curry powder.
Add chopped green pepper, onions and olives to cooled rice.
Add mayonnaise dressing and cut up artichoke hearts to rice salad.
Decorate with fresh tomato wedges on platter around salad.
Serves 8.

title: norm's bread
directions: Place yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in quart bowl.
Add warm (95° to 98°) water.
Let set 20 minutes or double in size.
In large bowl, place rest of ingredients.
Mix and add yeast/sugar/water mixture.
Mix and knead by hand until smooth and light texture. Cover and let rise 45 minutes in warm location (or double in size).
Divide into 5 equal parts.
Fold and place in bread pans. Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute green pepper in 2 tablespoons oil in skillet; remove pepper.
Add remaining oil.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk, green pepper, mushrooms, chicken and peas.
Cook just long enough to heat thoroughly.

title: vegetable gratin
directions: In a small bowl, combine mustard, oil and spices.
Mix 1 tablespoon mustard mixture with bread crumbs. Set aside.
In lightly greased 9-inch pie plate, arrange layer of half of the zucchini, overlapping slices.
Dot zucchini with some of the mustard mixture.
Layer half of the tomatoes, dotting with mustard mixture. Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Repeat layers as above. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes until veggies are tender. Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes until crumbs are golden brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread.
Add 1 can cream-style corn.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Season with taco seasoning and tomatoes.
Heat skillet with oil.
Add 1/2 cornbread mix; top with hamburger mixture. Cover with cheese.
Add remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: autumn pumpkin butter
directions: Combine pumpkin puree, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and nutmeg in a slow cooker; mix well.
Cook on high until thickened to desired consistency.
Spoon into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal with 2 piece lid and process 10 minutes.
Yields 4 pints.

title: pecan pie(makes one 8-inch pie)
directions: Make and bake pastry shell and leave light tan.
Cream together butter, sugar, eggs (one at a time), vanilla, salt and syrup.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Fill the pie shell.
Lay pecan halves flat side down all around top of pie.
Bake at 375° for about half an hour.
Test with a knife blade in center.
If it comes out clean, pie is done.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream or with whipped topping after it has cooled.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook ground beef with onion; drain.
Add chilies, Ranch dressing, taco seasoning, mix well, then add tomatoes, corn, beans, water, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with tortillas.

title: elegant chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve on lettuce or other greens.

title: fun cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed, just to moisten, then beat 8 minutes at medium speed.
Line a 10-inch tube pan with brown paper.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool right side up in pan for 15 minutes, then remove and cool.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Mash ripe bananas with a fork in a big bowl.
When soft, beat them with a rotary beater.
Add cold milk and vanilla and beat until drink is very frothy.
Dust with nutmeg.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hungarian gulyas
directions: Cut meat into squares.
Wash.
Saute onion in lard; add paprika.
Stir well.
Add meat, salt, diced tomato and 1/4 cup water.
Cook slowly 1 hour.
Add washed and diced vegetables, except potatoes.
Add 1 cup water and cook slowly for 1/2 hour. Add potatoes and continue to cook for 15 minutes.
Add 1 quart cold water.
Let it come to a boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve as main dish.
Dumplings can be added.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onion and squash. Drain. Mix 1/2 package stuffing with the melted margarine.
Add squash and onion and soup to stuffing mixture. Put in casserole and top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in covered skillet until soft.
Uncover and add salt and sugar; cook 15 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook 3 minutes longer.
Combine onions, consomme, water and wine in a crock-pot.
Cook on low 6 hours or high for 3 hours.
Serve in bowls with bread and cheese melted on top.
This recipe is doubled.
Cut it in half for a smaller portion.

title: chinese style country ribs
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; brush on both sides of ribs. Place in slow cooker on low.
Pour remaining sauce over all. Cover and cook 8 to 10 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: flowers and decorating frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam. Arrange 1/4 inch slices of sugar cookies on pizza pan. Bake according to directions. Cream together the cream cheese, sour cream and sugar. Spread mixture over cooled cookie crust. Next spread pie filling over mixture. Arrange various sliced fruit on pie filling in decorative fashion. Sprinkle with Fruit Fresh.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first two ingredients to 230° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Beat in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.

title: green enchiladas
directions: In blender, mix first 4 ingredients.
Add cream and egg; blend at low speed.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Set sauce aside. Soften cream cheese and mix in chicken and green onions.
Heat the sauce slowly and while doing this heat about 4 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Fry each tortilla lightly; dip it in the warmed sauce. Fill each tortilla with about 3 tablespoons cream cheese mixture; roll up.
Place (open edge down) in an oblong baking dish; pour half the remaining sauce over them.
Heat the enchiladas in a slow oven; serve them with the rest of the sauce and a side dish of sour cream.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine green beans, peas, pimientos, green pepper, celery and onion.
Mix together in separate bowl the sugar, vinegar and salt. Pour over vegetables and let stand 12 hours in refrigerator. Serve cold.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Bake shells according to package directions.
Melt butter. Add chopped green onions.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add flour; simmer 4 minutes.
Blend in soups.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add crawfish tails. Cook 15 to 20 minutes until done.
Spoon into pastry shells and serve.

title: upside down pizza loaf
directions: In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat 1/2 teaspoon oil.
Add turkey and onion, using the back of a wooden spoon to crumble meat.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender and the meat is no longer pink.
Sprinkle mixture with 1 tablespoon flour and combine, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce, pepper and Italian seasonings and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook stirring frequently, about 1 minute.

title: ham and broccoli birds in mustard sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place a broccoli spear in middle of each cheese-lined ham slice.
Roll up tightly and place in shallow baking dish, seam side down.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour, mustard seed and celery seed.
Cook, stirring every 1 to 2 minutes for 5 minutes.
Slowly add milk and bring to boil, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Pour over ham rolls and sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in baking dish and cover with chopped parsley and cornflakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serve with a sauce of stove-heated cream of mushroom soup spooned over the top of each serving.
Serves 8 people.

title: peggy's chocolate cake
directions: Mix the sugar and flour; set aside.
Mix the oleo, oil, water and cocoa; bring to a boil, then add flour and sugar mix.
Beat in the eggs, soda, vanilla and buttermilk; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Add topping.

title: passion jello
directions: Prepare
Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
When almost set up, add 1 can blueberry pie mix and sour cream.
Return to refrigerator to complete geling.
Serves 8.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Mix biscuit dough according to package directions.
Put dough on wax paper.
Put another piece on top.
Pat dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Remove top paper.
Cut dough into 3 x 4-inch strips.
Roll a piece around each hot dog.
Let the tip show at each end.
Pinch the end of the dough to seal it.
Put on cookie sheet, sealed edge down.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples.
Cut in slices and arrange in pastry lined pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar mixed with the cinnamon.
Sift remaining 1/2 cup sugar with flour. Cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 40 more minutes or until apples are tender. Serve warm or cool.

title: no boiling lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In bowl, combine Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan and eggs. In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread 1 cup meat sauce. Layer 4 uncooked noodles, then 1 cup sauce and 1/2 of the Ricotta mixture; repeat. Top with remaining 4 uncooked noodles and 2 cups sauce. Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake 1 hour. Remove foil and sprinkle with remaining cheeses. Bake, uncovered, an additional 10 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serve with remaining sauce, heated. Makes 12 servings. Prep time: 10 minutes. Cook time: 70 minutes.

title: plum sauce
directions: Wash and pit the plums.
Stew them in the vinegar with the cloves and sugar until they are tender.
Remove the cloves and puree the mixture in a blender or food processor.
Put the sauce in a saucepan, and add the mint.
Reheat.
If you find the sauce is a little too sharp, add more sugar.

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Make into small balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Press flat with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli mandarin salad
directions: Toast slivered almonds; cut red onion into 1/8-inch slices. Combine with broccoli, raisins, bacon, mushrooms and oranges.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts. Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly brown. Cool.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Mix All Bran Buds and boiling water; let stand 1 hour.
Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add Bran Flakes and soaked Bran Buds.
Keeps 6 weeks in Tupperware in refrigerator. Raisins and nuts may be added.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles until done; drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan mix soup, milk, chicken, butter, salt and pepper.
Add noodles and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, mandarin oranges, eggs and oil; beat for 2 minutes at highest speed of electric mixer.
Reduce speed to low; beat 1 minute.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove layers from pans.
Let cool completely.

title: microwave pork casserole
directions: Place pork in 2-quart glass casserole dish with salt and pepper.
Cover with water and microwave, covered, on High for 40 minutes.

title: chicken green chili casserole
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Layer half the chips, half the chicken, half the tomatoes, half the soup and half of the cheese.
Repeat procedure.
Microwave on High.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes on Full power.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Trim top layer of fat from meat.
Place several pieces of this fat in a Dutch oven.
Heat.
When bottom of pan is lightly covered with fat, remove fat.
Sprinkle short ribs with salt. Brown all sides and remove from pan.
Add onion and saute until lightly browned.
Return meat and add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: heather's pie
directions: In a bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in pecans.

title: lynda gaudette's three bean salad
directions: Stir together green beans, wax beans and red kidney beans. Add onions, if desired. Combine remaining ingredients and toss together with beans. Chill overnight. Stir a couple of times to blend flavors.

title: oven pancake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Mix all the rest with beater and pour into butter and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with sugar after it is baked.
Should be golden brown and raised when baked.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Pound meat with hammer.
Melt shortening in a skillet.
Add meat, brown on both sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: weight watchers pie
directions: Measure milk in mixing bowl.
Add boxes of pudding mix.
Beat on low until mixture thickens.
Add tub Crystal Light and mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: In first bowl, cream together the margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
In second bowl, combine pudding mix and milk.
Blend in Cool Whip and mix gently.
Combine both mixes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate container, mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix together all ingredients, then add to first mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped nuts. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make golf ball sized cookies. Bake at 275° until light brown.

title: fresh blender applesauce
directions: In a blender (food processor) fitted with metal blade, combine apples, water, lemon juice, sugar and cinnamon (if desired). Process until mixture is smooth.
If you want to serve warm, transfer to saucepan and bring to a boil or microwave for 3 minutes.
If you want to serve cold, cool, cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spinach ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare ziti according to directions on package; drain well.
Combine ziti, pasta sauce, Ricotta cheese and 3/4 of Mozzarella cheese.
Mix well.
Add spinach, mushrooms and black pepper; mix well.
Put mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and smooth top with a spoon.
Cover with foil and bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 of Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for about 10 more minutes.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Arrange chicken, skin up, in a shallow dish.
Combine soy sauce, sherry, sugar, garlic and ginger.
Pour over chicken. Marinate 2 hours, turning once.
Preheat broiler.
Spray rack with oil.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat, turning once and basting, about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round layer pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pans.

title: gingerbread muffins(low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 12-cup muffin tin with margarine.
Combine flours, sugars, baking soda, salt and spices in a large bowl.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine buttermilk, oil, egg, egg white and molasses.
Add flour mixture to buttermilk mixture.
Do not overmix.
Pour into cups of muffin pan and bake for 15 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Preparation:
Assemble ingredients and utensils needed. Separate eggs.
Chop nut meats coarsely.
Combine, in a saucepan, sugar, light corn syrup and water.
Cook, stirring, until sugar dissolved, then cook over low heat, without stirring, to hard ball stage (265°).
Test by dropping a few drops in a cup of cold water.

title: mayo parmesan bread
directions: Mix and spread on French or Italian bread slices. Place under broiler until lightly browned.

title: fruit chaat
directions: Take a dish and open the chick peas into it.
Peel and cut bananas in thin slices.
Peel and slice apples and then cut in small pieces about 1 inch big.
Do the same with the pears.
Do not peel, only slice and cut apricots the same size as apples.
Then, empty the pomegranate, after peeling, in the pan.
Cut grapes (seedless ones) into halves and mix.
Open the pineapple can and pour about 1 inch size pineapple chunks in the mixture.
Take the freshly squeezed orange juice and mix in the fruits.
Add lemon juice, salt, sugar and pepper.
Add these ingredients to your taste.
Eat and thank me!

title: fruited acorn squash(no fat)
directions: Cut each squash in half crosswise; remove and discard seeds. Place squash halves, cut side down, in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan lightly coated with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Combine pineapple, orange and brown sugar; spoon evenly into squash halves.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 10 to 15 minutes, or until fruit mixture is thoroughly heated.
If desired, garnish with orange rind curls and cinnamon sticks.
Yields 4 servings.

title: luscious lemon dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and jello in hot water.
Cool slightly.
Add cream cheese and stir until well blended.
A few chunks of cheese and marshmallow will still remain.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts. Chill until firm.
Serves 10.

title: lentil soup
directions: Put all in soup kettle, except parsley. Bring to
a boil, then simmer gently 1 hour.
Add parsley. Continue at low.
Simmer until lentils are very soft. Crush some lentils to make thicker soup. Serve with boiled frankfurters, or better still, bratwurst, sliced.
Pass red wine vinegar to add to soup at table.

title: chip and dorito dip
directions: Chop onions, tomatoes and olives into small pieces.
Grate cheese.
Cover bottom of small casserole dish with 1/2 container of sour cream.
Top with grated cheese, chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Next, cover with other 1/2 container of sour cream. Again, top with grated cheese, chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt
margarine.
To
this,
add soup and mix with hash browns,
cups
of
cheese,
sour
cream,
salt
and pepper. (Reserve
cup of cheese.) Place in long baking dish and top with the 1 cup of cheese.
Add corn flake crumbs on top of the cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chewy coconut-raisin nut cookies
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and eggs in
large
bowl.
Stir
in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough
by teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until
light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute
before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and rice dinner(crock-pot)
directions: Combine rice, soups and water in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into crock-pot.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in margarine.
Arrange over rice mixture.
Drizzle with remaining margarine.
Cook on low for 9 hours or longer.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: yummy pineapple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Put ingredients in pan.
Add enough water to cover frozen haddock.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain haddock.
Sprinkle with a little paprika and put under broiler for a few minutes to dry out. Serve with lemon and melted garlic butter.

title: french toast for a crowd
directions: The evening before serving, place the melted oleo, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
On this, place 8 to 10 slices of trimmed bread and stack 2 deep. Beat eggs well with milk and vanilla.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
As you serve, invert portions on plate. Makes own sauce.
Delicious!

title: bluefish
directions: Wash fish.
Set on pan skin side down.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread on fillet.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and paprika.
Broil until flaky (5 to 10 minutes, depending on thickness of fillet).
Watch so that topping doesn't burn.

title: cocido vegetalas (vegetable stew)
directions: Put all ingredients into a saucepan; cover with water.
Cover with lid and cook until done.
It will take about 30 minutes. Drain the liquid before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole with crunchy topping
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift flour once and measure. Add baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Cream shortening; add sugar and cream well. Add egg and beat well. Add flour alternately with applesauce, mixing thoroughly. Add raisins, nuts and oats; blend. Drop from teaspoon on greased baking sheet 2 inches apart. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Drain cherries thoroughly and place in bottom of one unbaked pie shell.
Combine whipping cream (do not beat), sugar, flour, salt and flavoring; pour over cherries.
Cut remaining pie shell into strips and crisscross over filled pie.
Bake in preheated 350° gas oven 50 to 60 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine the sugar and 2 cups water; heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Mix the dry drink mix and 1 quart water.
Put all the ingredients in a gallon jug and mix well.
Add water to fill gallon jug.

title: southwestern beef tacos
directions: Overnight marinade performs double duty, gently flavoring and tenderizing this lean cut of beef.
It can be grilled to perfection in only minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt bars in microwave or on stovetop.
Melt with syrup; cool. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine all dry ingredients with buttermilk, then add other mixture and vanilla.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Hershey's hot fudge sauce and vanilla ice cream.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Place soups and butter in 2 1/2-quart casserole and place in 350° oven until butter is melted.
Add water chestnuts, mushrooms and rice with seasonings.
Stir to mix and return to 350° oven for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine; drain.
Meanwhile, in large skillet, heat oil.
Add zucchini, red and green pepper strips and garlic. Saute just until vegetables are tender.
Blend in cream.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Heat through until slightly thickened, but do not boil.
Toss with hot cooked fettuccine. Makes 6 servings.

title: papa's prune cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed. Put in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 300° until sides shrink and top springs back, 45 minutes or longer.

title: strawberry almond bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and berries together and add to dry ingredient mixture and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Makes one large loaf pan or 3 small loaf pans.

title: my favorite sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add sour cream; fold in flour that has been mixed with soda.
Add flavor.
Bake in tube pan, greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: catfish stew
directions: In a large pot, brown fatback; remove and drain.
Add onions and potatoes and cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, catsup and drained fatback and cook for 10 minutes.
Add fish and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered, and on low heat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice or with hush puppies.
Serves 5 to 7.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Chop the tomato, onion and peppers.
Add the remaining ingredients to the mixture.
Let stand for at least 1 hour.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is coarse meal.
Stir in oats.
Sprinkle water evenly over surface.
stir with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Shape dough into a ball.
Chill.
Roll to fit 9-inch pie pan.
Makes one 9-inch pastry shell.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add pumpkin and juice.
Sift dry ingredients and spices together.
Blend into mixture.
Stir in nuts, raisins or dates.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: garden veggie dip
directions: Combine yogurt and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Add carrot and next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Yields 1 cup, plus 1 tablespoon.
Contains 11 calories per tablespoon.

title: hamburger stir-fry
directions: Fry hamburger in 9-inch skillet; drain.
Add vegies.
Let simmer.
Add the eggs, whipped, into mixture.
Cook Minute rice according to box directions.
Pour soy sauce into rice.
Mix hamburger and vegies into rice.
Eat.

title: green chillies enchilada casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk and Velveeta in top of double boiler until cheese is melted. Add green chillies and pimentos. Combine Longhorn cheese, onions and meat.
Fill each tortilla with mixture and roll tightly.
Place in a long baking dish.
Pour sauce over the top. Cover. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken wings
directions: Dissect wings.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix all other ingredients well.
Pour over wings in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 1 hour at 350°, then 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: sugarless candy
directions: Mix well.
May need to use your hands.
Make into rolls and refrigerate; after cooled and set, slice.

title: apple pudding
directions: Mix together apples and sugar, then add egg.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to apple mixture and mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: icebox angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut Crisco into flour. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to mix.
Add buttermilk and knead.
Store in plastic bag in icebox and use as you need it.
Do not let rise. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: easy cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Stir in flour; continue stirring until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat and beat in eggs one at a time.
Spread on a small greased cookie sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Cool away from draft.
Put a dish towel on top when cool and pat down lightly.

title: golden blueberry muffins
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and salt and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Combine buttermilk and baking soda, stirring well.
Add buttermilk to sugar mixture alternately with flour mixture, stirring just to combine.
Combine berries and 1/2 cup flour and gently fold into batter.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen muffins.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuits(aunt mary)
directions: Mix all together and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dewberry cobbler
directions: Mix dewberries and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside. Mix biscuit, sugar and milk well. Butter baking dish. Pour in mixture then add dewberries. Bake for 1 hr. at 350°. Pour butter and cinnamon on top.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Let cookie dough get to room temperature.
Spread out on pizza pan and bake according to package directions.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and enough milk so that it will mix well.
Spread on the dough.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Add sliced fruit. Spread crushed pineapple over this.
Spread marmalade on the top and chill until ready to serve.

title: ol' fashion farm fry
directions: Fry bacon, then crumble and drain all but 1 teaspoon of grease off.
Add cubed potatoes and chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Fry until potatoes are golden, then sprinkle with cheese and add eggs on top of mixture.
Stir over low heat until eggs are cooked. Serves 4.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Unroll the crescent roll dough; pat into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Pinch edges together to seal. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: country buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add buttermilk; blend well.
Turn onto floured surface. Knead gently several times.
Pat out to 1/4-inch thickness. Spread with half the butter.
Fold over to form 2 layers.
Brush top with remaining butter; cut with biscuit cutter.
Place 1/2-inch apart in greased 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, cube and cook eggplant; drain and mash.
Mix with soup, egg, onion, mayonnaise, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of cracker crumbs. Pour in buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove shells from shrimp, leaving shell on tail.
Devein.
Wash thoroughly.
Drain on paper towels. Melt oleo in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in oven.
Add salt, garlic and 1 tablespoon of parsley.
Mix well.
Arrange the shrimp in single layer in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Turn shrimp; sprinkle with lemon peel, lemon juice and remaining parsley.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Arrange on serving platter.
Pour garlic butter over all.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Roll all 10 biscuits together until about 1/4-inch thick. Spread sausage all over biscuits.
Roll into log.
Chill, slice and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Pour pineapple mixture into greased baking dish; crumble bread on top. Add margarine slices on top of bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: liver and onions(for weight watchers only)
directions: Place beef bouillon in pan with water.
Slice and saute onions until golden brown.
Push aside and cook liver lightly on both sides.
Do not overcook.
Weigh liver and onions.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in fat over low heat until onion is transparent, but not browned, stirring occasionally.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook apples according to package directions.
Add butter and allspice to cooked apples.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.
Serves 16.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese.
Mix well.
Add Bisquick a little at a time and mix with sausage and cheese.
If too dry, add a little water (1 tablespoon at a time).
Form into bite size balls. Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: "magic" rainbow cookie bars(makes 24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; chill if desired.
Cut into bars.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones and flake with fork. Mix cream cheese until creamy. Add lemon juice, lemon rind, onion, spices, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Stir in flaked salmon. Add salt if more is needed to taste. Combine chopped pecans and parsley and spread on waxed paper. Form salmon into ball and roll in nut mixture, until coated on all sides. Makes 10 servings, and may be made a day ahead. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread, meat and cheese; beat remaining ingredients and pour over top (it is better if refrigerated overnight before baking).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in greased 9 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
A family Christmas tradition!

title: brownie pizza
directions: Bake brownie mix in a 12-inch deep dish pizza pan at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.
Check occasionally as brownie mix will be spread thinner than usual and may become crisp before you know it.
Using mixer, combine milk, cream cheese and concentrate in a bowl; chill slightly.
Spread over cooled brownie pizza.
Top with whole cherries, pecan halves and chopped pecans.
Melt chocolate chips and drizzle over pizza.
Refrigerate.
(May substitute other fruit for cherries, such as strawberries and bananas.)

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a simmering boil.
Mix 6 cups Special K cereal, 1 1/2 cups crunchy peanut butter and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Mix with syrup and form into small balls.
Keep in airtight container.

title: orange cookies
directions: Drop on greased pan with teaspoon.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes at 300° or until brown.

title: chicken and cheddar cheese soup and tomato sauce
directions: Skin chicken and brown in oil with peppers and onions.
Mix tomato sauce and soup.
Put chicken in dish; add peppers and onions.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Enjoy.

title: stewed greens and ham hocks(makes 4 servings)
directions: Wash greens thoroughly.
Pick over and chop coarsely.
Set ham hock to boil in water enough to cover.
When water boils, add greens and seasoning.
Reduce heat to a high simmer and cook 2 to 3 hours, adding water if needed.
Serve with cornbread.

title: chocolate pinwheels
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together shortening, Sweet 'N Low and egg.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add to flour mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.
Divide dough in half.
Add melted chocolate to one half of dough.
Roll each half very thin.
Put one on top of other.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Chill overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: french pineapple cream cake(12 servings)
directions: Put 1/2 of cake mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake a thin layer. (Make cupcakes out of rest.)
Cook the vanilla pie filling, or make a 3-cup cream pie filling recipe.
Stir into hot filling the cream cheese.
Pour over cooled cake layer.

title: mexican rice
directions: Place
quartered
tomatoes,
onion, garlic and 2 tablespoons water in
blender.
Wash
rice and let drain.
Heat oil in deep heavy two-quart saucepan.
Add rice, stir over medium heat until each rice kernel is golden brown.
Add ingredients from blender and
continue
to
stir
for
a few minutes.
Add boiling water slowly
and
carefully as steam will rise.
Add salt and peas. Cover.
Simmer
minutes (do not lift cover or stir).
The rice
should
have
absorbed all the water and will be dry and flaky.
Makes six servings.

title: coconut cream cheesecakes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; firmly press evenly onto bottom and 2 inches up sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese at high speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar; beating well.
Add egg yolks and eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in coconut and next 3 ingredients; pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Center will be soft.
Turn oven off and leave cake in oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool at room temperature on a wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Carefully remove sides of pan.
If desired, top each serving with whipped cream and toasted coconut.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sinful sundae pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie pan with whole cookies.
Combine milk, marshmallows, chocolate chips and salt in saucepan.
Cook and stir until blended and thick.
Cool slightly. Spoon half of ice cream into shell.
Drizzle half sauce over ice cream; repeat.
Return to freezer immediately and chill for 4 hours.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients, add milk and egg gradually. Stir in apples.
Fry in deep, hot fat until golden brown.
Serve with powdered sugar.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage rye bread goodies
directions: Cook sausage in frypan.
Drain well.
Add cheese and paprika and mix well.
Spread on rye bread.
Broil in oven until edge of bread looks toasted, 3 to 4 minutes.
Makes 36 rounds and freezes well.

title: garden salad
directions: Bring last 6 ingredients to a boil.
Cool and pour liquid over the vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix Quik and food coloring together until Quik is dissolved. In a separate bowl, mix cake mix, eggs and water until well blended.
Stir in food coloring mixture.
Mix well.
Add 1 package dry Dream Whip.
Bake according to directions on cake mix box.

title: beet jelly
directions: Stir together juice,
Sure-Jell
and jello.
Bring to a boiling point and add sugar.
Boil good for 1 minute.
Pour in jars and seal.
(Prick beets with fork to let juice out.)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except corn flakes and butter.
Pour in casserole dish.
Mix soft or melted margarine with corn flakes and spread on top.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: cucumber delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be frozen.

title: layered cheese log
directions: Roll Velveeta cheese between two pieces of waxed paper with rolling pin until smooth and shaped to fit serving dish (should be about 1/4 inch thick).
Remove top layer of wax paper.
Spread cream cheese evenly on Velveeta.
Spread other ingredients in the order given.
Using wax paper to guide you, fold 1/3 of cheese over and then 1/3 from other side over the top of that.

title: dinner in
directions: Select desired foods from the directory (arguing optional). Using the telephone, dial Take Out Taxi's number.
State food request slowly and clearly (multi-lingual abilities may be helpful).
Prepare table, using dishes, etc.
(Eating directly from food containers may be preferred.)
Open and check the quality of the wine (several times, as necessary).
Answer door bell; pay with cash, folding in the tip.
Enjoyment of meal is directly related to quantity of wine consumed.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Beat egg slightly and add to mixture.
Shape in pan, bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: north german onion tart("zwiebel kuchen")
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease an 11-inch quiche pan; set aside.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat; add jello, stirring until dissolved. Gently stir in berries. Pour into pastry shell and chill. Serve with whipped topping.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, soups and sour cream.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Pour in chicken mixture and top with crackers.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine bread crumbs, salt, pepper, parsley, garlic and almonds.
Dip chicken in egg whites and then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle with a few slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6. Contains 233 calories, 842 mg sodium, 6 gm fat and 22 gm protein.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar and salt in double boiler.
Pour scalded milk over this mixture.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add hot mixture very slowly to beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Return to double boiler.
Cook 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Add vanilla.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: In a plastic sealable container, place broccoli flowerets, jar of pimiento, plus garlic on a toothpick.
Mix vinegar and oil to taste, I use half and half.
Stir.
Shake dill weed to cover top. Seal and chill overnight, turning the container over from time to time.
Pretty at Christmas for a potluck.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening good.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixed sugar and shortening (cream good again).
Roll graham crackers very fine and add salt and baking powder to rolled crackers.
Add nuts, then combine with beaten yolks and sugar, adding milk gradually.
Mix thoroughly, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 layers in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter tube pan or Bundt pan well. Sprinkle 1/3 of cinnamon/sugar mixture in pan, making sure to cover tube well.
Mix first 6 ingredients for cake batter.
Pour in 1/2 of batter.
Sprinkle 1/3 cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Pour in rest of batter and finish up with the cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Invert on plate.

title: brown bag apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toss apples with lemon juice in a bowl. Arrange apples in the pastry.
In a small bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix well. Sprinkle over apples.
Combine remaining sugar and flour.
Cut butter into mixture to make coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples. Slide pie into a large brown paper grocery bag.
Fold end over twice and secure with paper clips.
Put on baking sheet.
Bake for 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pasta with bread crumbs, garlic, anchovies and artichokes
directions: Saute garlic in oil. Add bread crumbs until golden.
Add tomatoes, parsley, artichokes and pasta water, if needed.
Add cooked pasta and toss.

title: quick turkey nachos
directions: In skillet, brown turkey; drain.
Add taco seasoning and water. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Place the tortilla chips on a greased baking sheet.
Layer turkey, sour cream and salsa.
Sprinkle the cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and onions.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Foil line a 10 or 12-inch clay flower pot.
Mix Cool Whip with cream cheese.
Layer pudding and Cool Whip into flower pot.
Put crushed Oreos on top to resemble dirt.
Add artificial flower and a spoon.

title: christmas angel cake
directions: Prepare angel food cake mix as label directs, baking it in an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Cool cake as directed, then store, carefully covered.

title: chocolate cream fudge cake
directions: Cook 2 layers and let them cool.
Then split them.

title: whole wheat pretzels
directions: On the floured pastry sheet, roll the dough into a 12 x 6-inch rectangle.	If
dough
is difficult to handle, let rest for 10 minutes.
Cut
into
12 (6 x 1-inch) strips.
Roll into ropes 14-inches long.
Shape
each
pretzel
by crossing 1 end over the other to form a circle, overlapping about 3 1/2-inches from each end.
Take	1
end	in
each
hand and twist once where dough overlaps.
Carefully
lift end across to opposite edges of circle. Moisten
and
press ends under edges.
Place the pretzels 1-inch apart on a well greased baking sheet.
Let stand, uncovered, for 20	minutes.
In
a
small	bowl,
beat together the egg
and
the water.
With a pastry brush, brush tops of pretzels with egg mixture.
Sprinkle with sesame seed, poppy seed, toasted wheat germ or dried minced onion.
Bake at 350° for 18 to
minutes or	until
golden brown.
Remove; cool on a wire
rack.
Store
in an airtight container.
Will freeze up to 8 months.
Makes 12 pretzels.

title: hush puppies(silent dogs)
directions: No salt or pepper as this will come from the oil when fish are cooked.

title: vermont beans
directions: Cover bottom of casserole with celery and onion.
Combine pork and beans, celery seed, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and pepper sauce.
Pour over celery layer.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover, top with onion rings and bake uncovered 5 minutes until onions are brown.
Serves 6.

title: shortbread (scottish)
directions: Originally this recipe was measured by weight and completely mixed by hand.

title: miniature pepperoni rolls
directions: Press individual biscuits with heel of hand.
Cut pepperoni into 2-inch pencil strips.
Place 1 strip pepperoni, 1 teaspoon cheese, piece of green pepper or broccoli.
Roll up, pinch ends. Bake according to directions on biscuit package.
Eat plain or dip in heated pizza sauce.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into small balls; roll in flaked coconut.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: hamburger barley chowder
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook 15 minutes in pressure cooker.

title: cajun steamed chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Sprinkle with red pepper. Do not flour the meat.
Have oil hot in pan, drop in chicken pieces and let get hot.
As it begins to brown; sprinkle sugar on chicken.
Add onion and bell pepper; stir while browning.
Pour water in while real hot, cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Stir often.
Cook until tender.
Pour over hot rice.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together in very, very large bowl.
Add oats, chips and M&M's by hand.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 1 month.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and eggs; blend well.
Dissolve soda in 3 tablespoons hot water.
Mix with sugar mixture.
Add 1 cup flour and salt; beat well.
Add bananas, remaining flour and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: peach float
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients.
Sift flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Beat smooth and pour into buttered baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or hard sauce.

title: spicy mixed nuts
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, milk and water in a 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Place over medium or medium-low heat and cook to the soft ball stage (236° to 238°), stirring constantly to prevent curdling.
Remove from heat; mix in nuts and vanilla.
Let stand 15 minutes, then stir with a wooden spoon until mixture thickens. Pour at once onto wax paper-lined baking sheet, spreading as thinly as possible.
When cool, break in bite-size pieces.
Store in covered container, in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes one pound.

title: maple bars
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to other ingredients.
Knead and let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out and cut into strips. Let rise a second time, then fry in hot fat.
Cool and frost with your favorite maplene frosting.

title: baked french toast
directions: Mix together whipping cream, eggs, and honey or syrup.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Place bread in dish then pour liquid over.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 mins.
Dot with butter while hot.
(I substitute skim milk and 1/2 egg whites.)

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa together.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and beaten eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Spoon into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Pour mix over cucumbers and let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Then take out, put in small plastic bags or containers and put in freezer.

title: radonna's ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, garlic powder, onion powder and parsley flakes.
Spread mixture evenly on ham.
Roll ham and chill.
When ready to serve, cut into bite size pieces.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add sugar, oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in flavorings, sweet potatoes, raisins and pecans. Pour into 3 greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until bread tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: curry pate
directions: Thoroughly blend cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, sherry, curry powder and salt.
(I do mine in the food processor.) Spread on a serving platter in a circle 1/2-inch thick.
Chill until firm.
At serving time, spread with chutney and sprinkle top with green onions.
Serve with crackers.

title: country style pork chops and carrots
directions: Cut carrots in half lengthwise.
Arrange in bottom of baking pan.
Cut onion crosswise into 8 slices.
Combine flour, salt, thyme and pepper.
Dredge chops in this.
Brown in shortening and arrange in pan over carrots.
Place onion slice on each.
Pour water over chops.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake in 350° oven until meat and carrots are done, about 1 hour.

title: baked red rice
directions: You will need 6 x 12-inch baking pan and aluminum foil.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and bacon until bacon is done.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in greased tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
While cake is baking, combine 1 cup orange juice and 2 cups powdered sugar. When cake is done and still hot, poke holes in top, pour mixture over cake.
Let set overnight.
May be wrapped well and frozen.

title: polynesian fruit punch
directions: Combine juices and lemonade and orange juice concentrate in a large punch bowl.
Blend well.
Pour in ginger ale.
Add ice cubes. Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: green bean mushroom casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Dilute cream of mushroom soup with milk. Then pour cream of mushrooms over the green beans.
Cover with a lid.
Bake in an oven for 40 minutes.
Bake at 350°.
Put dehydrated onions over the green beans.
Take lid off so that the dehydrated onions will be crispy.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients well; pack into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix eggs, salt and sugar lightly.
Add lemon juice.
Fold in flour and baking powder. Pour on top of crust.
Bake additional 25 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
When cooled, cut into bars.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion and cook until done (about 5 minutes).
Add all other ingredients except tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes; simmer another 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Drop by tablespoon on greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green bean delight
directions: Cook green beans the way you like them.
Put them in a baking dish; add onion rings that have been sauteed, cheese and bacon bits.
Put in oven and let bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°. (I like to use crispy fried bacon pieces instead of the bacon bits you buy.)

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour 4 ounces tomato sauce over top of all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: milk pops
directions: Mix chocolate syrup into milk, then pour into pop molds and freeze.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: Put oil in skillet; add chopped onion and tortillas.
Stir-fry over medium heat until tortillas are soft.
Add enchilada sauce and reduce heat.
Add corn and olives and heat through.
Add cheese and cook until melted.
Serve with refried beans.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on the box.
Melt margarine in iron skillet on top of melted margarine.
Dot with maraschino cherries.
Pour cake mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until tested with toothpick.
Turn upside down on plate to serve.
This cake is larger than a regular plate size. Use a meat platter plate.

title: fast - easy - low-fat dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and prepared instant pudding.
Break pieces of angel food cake. Layer 1/3 of cake at bottom of glass serving bowl.
Pour Cool Whip pudding mixture on top layer fresh fruit. Continue with 2 more layers, ending with Cool
Whip pudding mixture on top.
Add fresh fruit on top.

title: raisin carrot apple bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and lemon peel together until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add raisins, apples and carrots. Sift flour again with baking powder, baking soda and salt into the raisin mixture.
Stir until blended.
Turn into greased and floured loaf pan (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 3/4-inches).
Bake in slow oven at 325° for one (1) hour.
Makes one loaf of bread.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Blend well.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop dough on greased cookie sheet by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart.
Bake for 7-10 mins. until edges are light golden brown.

title: lasagna without noodles
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Cook peppers, onion and mushrooms until tender.
Add meat, tomato paste with seasonings and 1 can of water.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well. Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered, in a greased baking dish, until golden brown on top.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter together. Add the vanilla and stir in the Wheat Chex.

title: rum punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let stand at least 1 hour to blend.
Pour over ice in a punch bowl.
Makes about 75 glasses.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an uncooked deep pie crust. Top with a prepared pie crust and leave aluminum pan on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, then remove pie pan and bake for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: no-bake cookies(kids)
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Bring to rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until well blended. Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: texas eggs with ham
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk, salt and pepper (to taste).	Melt butter in large skillet and stir eggs to a medium scramble.
Add ham (or bacon) and stir in.
Spray a 9 x 13 casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Heat soup, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and add sherry.
Pour over cooked eggs.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
May refrigerate at this point.
Bring to room temperature before baking.	Bake at 250° uncovered for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: pink snow salad
directions: Beat chilled milk until stiff with electric mixer set at high speed. Add lemon juice. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Freeze in large covered container or smaller containers for serving.

title: stewed eggs
directions: Shell the eggs and place in saucepan with stewing sauce and water. Bring to a boil. Cover. Then turn heat to low and simmer for 1/2 hour or until cooked and sauce has flavored the eggs thoroughly. Remove and cool slightly. Serve with sesame oil and chopped green onions.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking pan (8 x 8-inch).
Mix 1 cup sugar with peaches.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large pot melt 1/4 pound butter. Add onion and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat until tender, stirring often.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Use additional seasoning if necessary.
Add milk; stir constantly over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Stir in cheese and remove from heat. Place potatoes in large baking dish.
Sprinkle pimentos over potatoes and mix lightly.
Divide thickened sauce between 2 dishes, pouring over each dish.
In medium bowl, mix bread crumbs, parsley and 2/3 melted butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over potatoes and bake 30 to 40 minutes until heated thoroughly.

title: chili chow wow
directions: Reserve 1 cup of corn chips and 1/2 cup of cheese.
In 2-quart baking dish, combine remaining corn chips, 1 1/2 cups cheese, salsa and chili.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, spread sour cream over top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese and border with reserved corn chips. Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples into 8 x 12 glass baking dish. Add 1 1/2 tablespoons cinnamon to 1/2 cup sugar and sprinkle over apples. Squeeze juice from lemon. Set aside.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased cake pan.

title: lemon squares
directions: Pour over baked crust and bake until set, about 20 minutes. Cool and cut.

title: cheddar broccoli bake
directions: Mix soup, milk, broccoli and 1/2 can onions in 1 1/2-quart dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot. Stir; sprinkle with remaining onions. Bake 5 more minutes. Serves 6.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook all ingredients except whipping cream until thick, cool. Add whipping cream; beat well.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mash broccoli a little.
Add remaining ingredients and microwave until hot.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar; add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together and add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Let dough set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon and sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry n' spice sauce
directions: In small
saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg;
gradually stir in water.
Cook stirring constantly over low heat
until
mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Add blueberries
and
continue
stirring,
just
until
sauce reaches a
boil
again.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in butter or margarine in heavy saucepot.
Add 2 cups water; bring to boil.
Cover; simmer until meat is almost tender, about 1 hour.
Add carrots and onions; cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add peas.
Cook 15 minutes longer, or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Drain meat and vegetables, reserving stock.
Refrigerate stock until fat hardens.
Cover meat and vegetables and refrigerate.
Remove and discard hardened fat.
Add enough water to make 4 cups stock.
Gradually blend about 1 cup stock into flour.
Pour into pot with remaining stock, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Mix in beef and vegetables.
Simmer about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: christmas special fruitcake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine nuts, dates and cherries.
In another bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; add to nut mixture, stirring until nuts and fruit are well coated. Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold into nut mixture. Mix well.

title: wellesly fudge cake
directions: Place chocolate and hot water in double boiler and cook and stir until chocolate is melted and thickened.
Add sugar; cook 2 minutes longer and cool to lukewarm.
Sift flour with soda and salt three times.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, beating thoroughly.
Add milk and dry ingredients.
Add chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball(makes 1 large cheese ball)
directions: Mix ingredients together using only 1 cup of the chopped pecans.
Roll the cheese ball in the remaining pecans, coating evenly.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken broth 15 minutes.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add flour; stir.
Add evaporated milk and sweet milk and cook until thick.
Add to broccoli.
Add paprika and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir often.

title: poached eggs in sauce
directions: Saute onion until transparent.
Add salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and water. Simmer on low heat for 5 minutes.
Drop eggs in sauce and cover.
Eggs may be cooked to desired taste: soft, medium or hard.

title: chocolate pineapple eclair cake
directions: Combine crushed pineapple with dry instant pudding. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan or two 9-inch round pans.
After cake is cool, split in two pieces. Add Cool Whip to pineapple pudding mixture, blending well.
Place mixture between layers of split cake.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave cheese out 3 to 4 hours, long enough to get soft.
Chop pecans very small; set aside.
When cheese is soft, combine until completely mixed together.
Add cayenne pepper, garlic and onion powder to taste.
Form into 1 big ball or several small.
Lay out wax paper and mix pecans and paprika together.
Roll ball over mixture.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 days.
Serve with crackers.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream together oil, butter, sugars and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together and add to creamed mixture.
Add pecans.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: nikki's taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasonings, cream cheese and sour cream with electric mixer.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Add layers of tomatoes, lettuce, cheese and olives.
Serve chilled.
Dip tortilla chips in dip.
Garnish with salsa and sour cream, if desired.

title: the ugly cake
directions: Pour cake mix in greased and floured pan. Mix remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls over cake mix and spread. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: betty's coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions on the side panel for a pound cake.
Take out of oven when it gets done; quickly punch holes in it with knife, then pour condensed milk over it.
Let cool.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.
Let sit in fridge overnight.
Use long loaf pan.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix spinach, cauliflower and cashew nuts.
Pour dressing over and refrigerate.

title: ripe tomato relish(good and easy!)
directions: Cut the tomatoes up fine; also apples, onions and peppers (food processor a big help).
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Mix in spices.
Cook together for about 2 hours in an open kettle.
Put in sterilized cans and seal.
(I keep in refrigerator.)
Very, very good and easy.

title: grapefruit congealed salad
directions: First peel and section grapefruit; sprinkle 9 tablespoons cold water over 3 packages Knox unflavored gelatine.
Dissolve sugar in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix with gelatine.
Add 3 cups sectioned grapefruit and 1 cup grapefruit juice.
Put 1/2 in a 9-inch square dish.
Congeal.
Leave other half at room temperature.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: For variety, add 3/4 cup raisins, chopped nuts, coconut or chocolate chips.

title: pumpkin souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pumpkin and flour.
Mix well until smooth.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Tear biscuits into chunks and put in Bundt pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, water and vanilla and pour over biscuits.
Slice stick of butter and
layer over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into a ball and sprinkle coconut over it or roll in pecans. Serve with butter cookies or graham crackers.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions.
Poke holes in cake and pour condensed milk and caramel topping over cake.
Let soak until cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Crush candy bars and sprinkle on cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oven asparagus
directions: Preheat
oven to 450°.	Combine all ingredients, except sesame seed,
in
jelly
roll
pan.
Cover
tightly with foil. Bake 7 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 7 minutes more or until just tender. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serves 4.

title: fiesta chuck roast
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Shake flour in 1 regular size Reynolds Oven
Bag,
place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add picante
sauce, onion and garlic.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Trim
fat from roast, place in bag.
Turn bag to coat roast
with
sauce.
Place
pepper
and
carrots in bag around roast.
Close
bag
with nylon tie.
Cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of
bag.
Bake
until
roast
