is tender, 1 3/4 to 2 hours. Let stand in bag 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ensalada guacamole
directions: Wash tomatoes, scoop out middle and save. Peel avocados and remove seeds. Mash in bowl; add 1/2 cup tomato pulp, jalapeno, onion powder, garlic powder, salt and lemon juice. Stuff into tomato shells and place on lettuce caps. Garnish with a dab of salad dressing. Sprinkle chili powder over all.

title: favorite uncooked tomato relish
directions: Combine tomatoes, celery, onion and salt; drain overnight in jelly bag.
The next day, add vinegar, sugar, peppers and mustard seed.
Stir.
Pour into sterilized glass jars with tight lids. Allow relish to age a minimum of 2 weeks before serving. Fills 12 to 16 small bell-style jars.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Stir the bread crumbs, Romano cheese, garlic, parsley, mint, salt and pepper to taste and 2 tablespoons olive oil in a medium bowl to blend.
Drizzle a heavy large baking sheet with about 1 tablespoon olive oil to coat. Spoon the filling into the mushroom cavities and arrange on the baking sheet, cavity side up.
Drizzle remaining oil over the filling in each mushroom.
Bake until the mushrooms are tender and the filling is heated through and golden on the top, about 25 minutes.
Serve.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground chuck, bacon and onions. Add other ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate scotcharoos
directions: Cook sugar and syrup in pan over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup peanut butter.
Mix in 7 cups Rice Krispies cereal and press into buttered cake pan and let harden.
In double boiler, melt over hot water chocolate chips and butterscotch chips until melted.
Spread over top of mixture.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a shallow 1-quart microwave-safe casserole or 8-inch round glass dish, combine brown sugar, butter and water.
Microwave on High power for 1 minute.
Stir to melt butter and dissolve sugar. Stir in nuts.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and add to sugar mixture.
Stir to coat each piece.
Use scraper to push mixture and biscuits evenly away from center.
Place a small empty custard cup or medium drinking glass in the center with open side up to form a ring mold.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn and microwave again on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until biscuits are no longer sticky.
Let mixture set for 1 to 2 minutes. Carefully remove custard cup and invert on a serving plate.
Serve immediately.

title: poppy seed torte
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together the crumbs, flour, butter and nuts.
Pat into a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake until light brown. Combine the milk, 1 cup sugar and beaten egg yolks into top of double boiler; beat until sugar is dissolved.
Add poppy seed, cornstarch and salt; cook until thick.
Dissolve gelatin in water; add to cooked mixture.
Cool.
Fold in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and cream of tartar; fold into cooled filling.
Pour into crust.
Top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoon into balls.
Roll in a mixture of sugar/cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake until set (approximately 8 to 10 minutes) at 400°.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: breaded tomato slices
directions: Combine eggs, milk, seasoned salt and dash of pepper.
Cut tomatoes into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Dip in cracker crumbs, then in egg mixture.
Dip again in crumbs.
In skillet, fry in hot oil until browned on both sides.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; cook over very low heat until cheese is nearly melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream sugar and shortening. Add milk and flour alternately. Blend well and add eggs and vanilla. In an oblong cake pan, melt margarine and sprinkle 1 cup sugar over this. Spread strawberries evenly in pan and pour batter over them. Bake until brown and slices are crusty (about 30 to 40 minutes).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken; remove from the bone and chop coarsely. Heat undiluted soup and cheese until melted.
Stir in chicken. Pour into a greased casserole dish; top with the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: bridal punch
directions: Chill all ingredients at least 24 hours prior to serving. Place ice cubes in large punch bowl.
Add cranberry juice, water and lemonade concentrate.
Stir in lemon lime soda.
Garnish with strawberries and lemon slices.
Float orange sherbet on top. Time: 10 minutes.
Serves: 20.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all together in blender on low; pour in greased large pie plate.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then lower heat to 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cook until a knife comes out clean.
Cream may be used as a garnish.

title: peanut butter delight pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream. Turn into a chocolate 9-inch pie crust.
Drizzle the chocolate syrup over top of pie and gently swirl with spoon.
Chill 4 hours.
Refrigerate any leftover. Serves 6 to 8.

title: nice 'n' cheesy
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Layer bread, 1/2 of the pasteurized process cheese spread, 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese, mushrooms and remainder of cheese.
Melt butter.
Add eggs and light cream.
Pour over layered ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour in a pan of water.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale, chill.

title: creole-style green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Add onion and green pepper to 3 tablespoons of drippings; cook until tender. Blend in flour, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add tomatoes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add beans; heat.
Top with bacon.

title: butterscotch pie with graham cracker crust
directions: Mix thoroughly and press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of crumbs for top of meringue.

title: french onion dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and thin down with milk.
Add beef base and dehydrated onions according to how you want it to taste.

title: italian shrimp
directions: De-head and wash shrimp; drain.
Put in large pot.
Pour salad dressing over shrimp.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a slow boil, turning often, until shrimp are pink.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Works well with low-calorie dressing also outside on grill.
Serves 4.

title: mushroom bacon bites
directions: Wrap each mushroom with a piece of bacon; secure with a toothpick. Thread onto metal or soaked bamboo skewers. Brush with barbecue sauce. Grill, uncovered, over indirect medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until the bacon is crisp and the mushrooms are tender, turning and basting occasionally with remaining barbecue sauce. YIELD: 2 dozen.

title: centennial casserole
directions: Cook noodles until barely done; drain.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix everything together and put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: economy cake
directions: Combine sugar, water, butter and raisins.
Boil together for 5 minutes, let cool.
Add soda, spices and flour.
Bake 3/4 to 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; cut into thin wedges.
Arrange in unbaked pie shell.
In small bowl, mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Layer apples and cinnamon-sugar mix.
Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Cover and remove from heat.
Fluff mixture after 10 minutes and let stand, covered, for 10 more minutes. Place half of mixture in greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Repeat layers and place in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for approximately 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake.
Dust cake with powdered sugar or make a glaze.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In saucepan, heat soups together.
In casserole dish, layer chips, chicken, soups, onion and cheese. Repeat.
Top with chips and cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and beaten egg yolks.
Add juice and milk; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Bake in glass pie plate so you can see the bottom to check for browning.
Bake on lower rack at 425° for 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Check for brownness.
Test along edge with butter knife; if it comes out clean, it is done.

title: cucumber salad
directions: The day before, scrub and peel cucumbers.
Slice thinly and put into a bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons salt in bowl of cucumbers. Press water from cucumbers by placing plate on top of cucumbers and placing a heavy can on top of plate for several hours.
Drain cucumbers and pat with a towel.
In another bowl, combine vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate covered cucumbers overnight.

title: cheese dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar with a good fitting lid; shake well before using.
Add to salad just before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tuna fish sandwich
directions: Drain tuna fish; put in bowl.
Mix all ingredients.
Put on bread.
Enjoy.

title: italian beef
directions: Put all of the above ingredients in a crock-pot on low for 12 to 14 hours or longer, if desired.
Serve on a kaiser bun.

title: ann's graham cracker delight
directions: Mix together and save some cracker crumbs for topping.
Put rest in bottom of pan.

title: mozzetti
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Fry hamburg and onion together; drain fat.
In a bowl, mix mushrooms, tomato soup, mushroom soup and tomato sauce together.
In a casserole dish, place in layers. Start with mixture (soup) to cover bottom of dish.
Add a layer of noodles, then a layer of hamburg mixture, then cheese.
Continue until ingredients are all used up.
End top layer with soup mixture; this prevents noodles from drying.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: panocha
directions: Put sugar and milk in heavy pan. Cook to soft ball stage, 238°.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Cool, without stirring, until lukewarm.
Beat until creamy. Stir in broken nuts and pour into buttered dish.
Pour before it turns white.

title: classic cheesecake(light)
directions: Combine margarine, graham crumbs and cinnamon and press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan and set aside.
Mix at medium speed the cream cheese until smooth.
At low speed, mix in slowly sour cream, sugar, egg substitute, vanilla, salt and ginger until blended.
Pour over graham crust and bake 45 to 50 minutes; center of cheesecake may be loose.
Cool in pan or on wire rack. Refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Place 30 (2 1/2 inch) paper liners in muffin cups.

title: nut bread - cranberry classic
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. In a bowl, mix together flour, sugar, orange rind, baking powder, baking
soda,
cinnamon,
salt,
ginger,
allspice and cloves. Add shortening, orange juice and molasses.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat for 2 minutes. Stir in cranberries, carrots and pecans.
Pour into pan and
bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice, vinegar, egg, sugar and flour.
Boil until thick.
When cool, add Cool Whip.

title: glazed peach cake
directions: Mix together; pour in a greased oblong pan.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Glaze while hot.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons ice water, then add 1 cup boiling water; let cool.

title: honey wheat oatmeal bread(for bread machine)
directions: Place in bread machine according to manufacturer directions.
Bake on basic or quick method.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll each piece of biscuit in cinnamon mixture and drop into a well-greased, large Bundt pan.
Between each can of biscuits that's placed in pan, sprinkle some pecans.
After layering, pour the remainder of the sugar over the biscuits.
Melt margarine and pour over sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: layered onion bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Pat dough in pan with floured hands, pressing dough 1/2-inch up sides.
Sprinkle 1 cup onions and 1 cup cheese over dough.
Mix eggs, soup, salt and pepper; pour over cheese and onions.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Crush remaining onions; sprinkle over top.
Bake until onions are golden brown and filling is set, about 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Cook meat and onion together; drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer a little while and serve hot on buns.
Serves 6.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Whip egg whites in large bowl (20 minutes);
alternating with sugar and strawberries until very stiff.
Gradually fold in cream by hand which has been whipped seperately.
Pour into large tube pan that has been prepared with graham cracker crust or you can use Lady Fingers.
Freeze overnight.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Add water to fill up a gallon jar after mixing ingredients. Add 1 bottle ginger ale when ready to serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, then add cherry pie filling, milk and Cool Whip.
Mix well together. Add pecans and marshmallows last.
You may add as many or as few of the marshmallows as you desired. Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: chicken pot pie(a "no-sift" recipe)
directions: Combine chicken and vegetables in well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour (not sifted), salt and pepper. Mix well. Add chicken stock gradually. Stir constantly.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens. Stir occasionally.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.

title: aunt rose's meat loaf
directions: Combine beaten eggs, salt, pepper, ginger and onion.
Add tomato juice, ground meat and oats; mix well.
Shape into loaf and place on sprayed rack in roaster pan.
Add 1/3 cup of water in bottom of roaster.
Cover.
Place in preheated 350° oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste 2 times.

title: powdered sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add powdered sugar; cream until light and fluffy. Beat in flour and eggs alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube cake pan. Bake in a 350° oven for at least 1 hour before checking.
Test for doneness.
Cake begins to pull away from sides, or toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Turn out on cake rack to cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir all ingredients together; bring to boil in a saucepan. Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: bunny salad(a great easter treat for your table!)
directions: For each serving, place crisp lettuce leaf on platter.
On top of it, place upside-down one chilled pear half.
Make bunny with narrow end for face facing center.
Eyes: 2 raisins.
Nose: One red cinnamon red hot candy.
Ears: Two blanched almonds. Tail:
Cottage cheese ball.

title: noodle stuffing
directions: Brown noodles on cookie sheet in oven (350°) until they are a golden brown color.
In skillet, saute chopped celery and mushrooms in a little oil.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, peanuts and brown sugar.
Mix well. Serve with apple slices.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour once, then measure.
Add baking powder and salt. Sift 3 times.
Rub in lard with fork and lastly, add milk.
Toss this on a well floured board and roll out a little less than a half inch thick; cut dough in rounds large enough to enclose a small apple.
Peel apples and core.
Place apple on dough, filling cavity of core with sugar, a dash of cinnamon and a small piece of butter. Press dough over apple and bake in a moderate oven.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Measure popped corn into a large heatproof bowl.
Place in a 300° to 325° oven to keep and crisp.
Combine sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and vinegar in a small saucepan.
Cook, covering with a tight lid the first few minutes of cooking, to dissolve sugar. Then remove lid and place thermometer in pan.
Cook to 250°.
Add flavor and color as desired.
Slowly pour syrup over hot popped corn.
Mix well until all the corn is well coated.
Shape into balls.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix raw peanuts, sugar, white Karo and boil over medium heat in skillet until honey colored and peanuts began to pop.
Remove from heat and stir in soda. Beat vigorously.
Work fast and pour on buttered cookie sheet. Allow to cool.
Break into desired pieces, and store in air tight container.

title: the cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Toss together 1 Tbsp cake mix, chocolate chips, and pecans.
Set aside.
Beat remaining ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Fold in chips and pecans.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: suzies specialty
directions: Brown beef and onions. Drain off fat. Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste. Add beans and simmer.

title: holiday poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up, in 2 clean 9-inch round cake pans.
Pierce cake with large fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve each flavor of gelatin completely in 1 cup boiling water in separate bowls.
Carefully pour red gelatin over 1 cake layer and lime gelatin over second cake layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours. Dip 1 cake pan in warm water 10 seconds; unmold onto serving plate.
Spread with about 1 cup of the whipped topping.
Unmold second cake layer; carefully place on first layer.
Frost top and sides of cake with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix meat mixture, soup, water, milk and cheese.
Fold in noodles that have been drained and set aside.
Place in casserole dish; sprinkle top with cheese.
Cook in 350° oven until it bubbles.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick margarine.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and other stick of margarine.
Add eggs and flour alternated with buttermilk mixed with soda.
Add melted candy and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour 10 minutes at 325°.

title: banana pineapple nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Combine eggs, bananas, oil, undrained pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Pour butter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 65 to 75 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: apple fry pies(method:  skillet)
directions: Mix dry ingredients; fold in shortening.
Beat together the egg and milk; add to dry mixture.
Stir until dough forms a ball. Divide into 6 portions; flatten each into a 5-inch circle.
Spoon apple filling onto 1/2 of circle; fold dough covering apple.
Seal edges with tines of fork.
Fry on greased griddle about 4 minutes on each side, turning once.

title: chicken breasts with lemon and capers
directions: Combine the flour, pepper and paprika on a plate.
Press the chicken into the mixture, coating them evenly all over and shaking off any excess.

title: cowboy beans
directions: In skillet, fry ground beef, onion, salt and sweet pepper. Drain ground beef. In large kettle, add all beans, cooked ground beef, tomato sauce and hot sauce as desired.
Cook, uncovered, on medium to low heat for about 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and tomato in a small amount of olive oil.
Add this to the cooked pasta in deep casserole dish.
Cut in crabmeat along with seasonings.
Fold in yogurt.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: sausage skillet supper
directions: In large skillet brown sausage, stirring to separate into small pieces.
Pour off any drippings in excess of 1/4 cup.
Add cabbage, water, salt and pepper to sausage.
Cover; simmer only until cabbage is crisp-tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles as directed; drain.
Add noodles to skillet; mix well with cabbage and sausage.
Heat together a minute or two, stirring constantly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk. Set aside. Mix sour cream and Cool Whip together. Add this to vanilla pudding. In a casserole dish, place 1 layer of bananas. Next place 1 layer of pudding on top of bananas; then 1 layer of vanilla wafers. Alternate layers ending with pudding mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash, onion, bell pepper and celery; saute in a small amount of oil.
Have about 1/2 loaf of dry bread crumbs (bread out of freezer is good).
Pour sauteed mixture over dry bread in large bowl.
Add egg(s).
Now, add chili.
Mix all together.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion, salt and pepper, covered with water, until tender.
In a bowl, mix meal, flour and sweet milk. Add to potato mixture; stir until slightly thickened.
If you wish, you may add 2 boiled eggs (sliced) before serving.
Good with corn bread muffins.

title: marinated beans
directions: Wash and drain beans.
Slice onion.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar, salt and oil.
Pour over beans and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over coarsely chopped apricots and allow to cool.
Beat the eggs until light and gradually beat in the sugar. Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add the dry ingredients and apricots alternately.
Add nuts.
Place in small greased bread pan and bake at 375° for 50 minutes; reduce heat to 350° for an additional 25 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In Pam sprayed casserole dish, cover bottom with hash brown potatoes.
Make sure potatoes are completely pressed and cover the casserole dish bottom.
Mix in bowl ham, cheese and diced green chilies.
Pour mixture of ham, cheese and diced green chilies over potatoes.
Beat the 6 eggs all together and pour over casserole, covering all the mixture.
(May have to use more eggs.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(May be longer with electric oven.)
Serve with biscuits and gravy or by itself.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix eggs, brown sugar, melted margarine, and milk well.
Add reminder of ingredients and blend.
Grease 1 - 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake 325° - 350° for at least 1 hour.
Stir 3 or 4 times while baking.

title: hot cross buns
directions: In a saucepan scald the milk.
Add the butter, honey and mashed potatoes.
Stir with a wire whisk or fork until the mixture is smooth and the butter melted.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: chalet ham dip
directions: Combine 1st four ingredients.
Slowly add milk, stirring until smooth.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven until 350°.
Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat until lemon color.
Add coarsely grated zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture; add nuts.
Oil and flour pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: country pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients all together in a bowl.
Pour into uncooked single crust.
Place pecans on top and cook on a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt, vanilla and butter flavoring; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.

title: mexican wedding cakes(international:  mexico)
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and vanilla extract.
Combine flour and salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly brown.
Roll warm cookies in sifted powdered sugar.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Serves 72.

title: herbed green beans
directions: Blanch beans in boiling, salted water for 2 to 3 minutes until not quite tender. Drain, refresh in cold water and dry. Saute garlic and onion in oil until tender, but not browned. Add tomatoes, beans and salt and pepper. Simmer 2 to 3 minutes until beans are tender-crisp. Add fresh herbs and cheese just before serving. Garnish with additional parsley. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar together.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oats, sugar and flour. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Place half of the mixture in greased baking dish. Cover with cranberry sauce. Spread rest of mixture over sauce.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal goodies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Add vanilla.
Sift the flour, soda, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture.
Add the oatmeal.
Roll into walnut size balls; dip into sugar.
Press flat with tines of fork.
Bake on oiled cookie sheets in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: irish cream liquor
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator up to one month. Stir before serving.
Return leftovers to refrigerator.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: In a saucepan warm milk and butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased crock-pot.
Top with slices of cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook on low for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. (If using a slow cooker it might take 4 hours.)

title: diet cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° about 45 minutes, depending on oven.

title: 24-hour cole slaw
directions: Slice or grate onions and cabbage.
Put into gallon glass jar. Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and mustard.
Bring to boil; remove from heat and add oil.
Mix well and pour over cabbage and onions. Cover tightly; set in refrigerator and let set for 24 hours.
Will keep a week if kept in refrigerator.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk until dough is sticky and stiff.
Sift 1/2 cup flour on wax paper.
Drop ball of dough and lightly pat it out to 1/2-inch thick.
(Do not knead.)
Cut out biscuits.
Bake in a well-greased skillet at 500°, preheated.

title: german crumb cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and reserve 1 cup.
Add rest of ingredients to remaining mixture.
After reserving 1 cup crumbs, add other ingredients and pour into oblong pan.
Sprinkle the cup of crumb mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or a variety of fruits. This is a good breakfast quick bread.

title: shrimp and artichoke casserole(serves 6)
directions: In small saucepan, melt 5 tablespoons of butter and stir in flour; blend well.
Add milk and cream, stirring constantly with wire whisk, until thick and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: frozen pops for kids
directions: Pour orange juice and water into mixing bowl.
Add pudding and beat until well mixed, about 1 minute. Pour into small paper cups. Freeze in refrigerator freezing compartment with control set for fast freezing, or in freezer.
When partially frozen, about 1 hour, insert wooden "pop" sticks.
Continue freezing until firm, about 1 more hour.
To eat, peel paper away.
Makes 5 to 6 "pops."

title: thai chicken fettuccine salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Combine picante sauce, peanut butter, honey, orange juice, soy sauce and ginger in small saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until blended and smooth.
Reserve 1/4 cup picante sauce mixture. Place fettuccine in large bowl.
Pour remaining picante sauce mixture over fettuccine.
Toss lightly to coat.
Cook chicken in oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until browned, about 5 minutes.
Add reserved picante sauce mixture; mix well.
Arrange fettuccine over lettuce-lined platter.
Top with chicken mixture. Sprinkle cilantro, peanut halves and pepper strips over top. Refrigerate to cool to room temperature.
Serve with additional picante sauce, if desired.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Cut butter pats and place in freezer 10 to 15 minutes before starting to cook.
Pound chicken breasts with tenderizer hammer until flat and thin.
Insert butter pat in center of each breast; add a dash of garlic salt, onion flakes and parsley.
Roll up each breast and pound edges to seal (may need toothpicks to hold together).
Dip each breast in beaten egg and then in corn flake crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, uncovered, until golden brown.
Turn them over if they get too brown on one side.

title: chicken with 40 cloves of garlic(makes 6 servings)
directions: Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry with paper towels. Set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream the butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix thoroughly.
Add bananas to flour mixture.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Best if you let bread sit overnight for best flavor.

title: wet choc-cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Combine 2 cups sugar and flour. Bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa, oil and 1 cup sugar.
Combine both mixtures and mix well. Add the buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: super simple terrace chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
While oven is preheating, wash chicken well.
Put in ovenproof pan and pour teriyaki sauce over it. Cover with foil and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In a large saucepan, melt peanut butter and butter or margarine.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Add cereal and mix well.
Shape into small balls and place on waxed paper; chill. Melt chocolate chips over low heat and stir in oil.
Dip the top of each ball in chocolate; chill.
Keep leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
Yield:
5 dozen balls.

title: herman doughnuts
directions: Combine all ingredients; roll onto floured board.
Cut; let rise about 1 hour.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: vegetable fried rice
directions: Add 1 tablespoon of oil to hot wok or skillet.
Add eggs and lightly scramble.
Remove eggs and add another tablespoon of oil. Stir-fry onions and garlic for 1 minute.
Add cold white rice, sugar and soy sauce.
Stir together until heated through.
Stir in vegetables and add scrambled eggs.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes(not granny mac's!)
directions: Drain
salmon;
set
juice
aside.
Mix salmon, egg and flour with fork, mixing well.
Mixture will be thick.
(Do not add salt; black pepper is optional.) Add baking powder to 1/4 cup
of reserved
salmon
juice and beat well.
Add to salmon mixture. Drop by tablespoon into hot oil;
cook until brown.

title: wassail bowl or spiced cider
directions: Put cider and juices in a 30 cup percolator.
Add sugar and spices in the coffee basket.
Let perk and serve hot from the coffee maker.

title: chicken divan
directions: Lightly brown chicken in 2 tablespoons butter, seasoning to taste with salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken over broccoli in a casserole.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Brown ground sirloin, bacon and onion together.
Drain off fat.
Add vinegar, white and brown sugar, dry mustard, catsup, kidney beans, butter beans, pork and beans and salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ham, potato and onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2 quart casserole dish. Put white sauce in saucepan; stir in salt, pepper and cheese. Cook over
medium heat, stirring occasionally until cheese is melted. Remove
from
heat;
stir in ham, potatoes and onion. Turn	into casserole
dish;
sprinkle with crumbs and butter. Bake 40 minutes.

title: down home hot dog chili
directions: Brown and drain chuck meat and onions, chopping with spatula while browning so the beef will be fine.
Add garlic clove, then add in this order:
tomato paste, tomato juice, barbecue sauce, sugar, mustard, garlic powder, parsley flakes, celery salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer 6 to 8 hours in slow cooker.
Yields approximately 4 quarts.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and cream of tartar together.
Add flour to butter and sugar, alternating with beaten egg whites.
Mix milk and soda, then add to butter, sugar and flour.
Flour fruit and mix into batter. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: healthy new england clam chowder
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add onion and saute until limp.
Add clam juice, water and potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add clams and milks.
Heat slowly over low heat about 45 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: beer bottom chicken
directions: Use beer at room temperature.
Pour about a inch out and place can upright on cookie sheet.
Cut any excess fat off of chicken.
Cover chicken with spices listed above.
Place bottom open cavity of chicken on beer.
Cook on grill on low for at least one hour or place on cookie sheet in oven (350) for an hour. Yeast in beer moistens chicken.
Remove chicken carefully from oven and use tongs to remove from can.

title: butterfinger chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Allow to cool, then punch holes in cake using the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour condensed milk over cake letting it seep into the holes.
Make sure the holes allow the milk to seep down through the cake.
Place in refrigerator to further cool; then spread the caramel topping over the top.
Cover with cool whip and add the Butterfinger sprinkles last.
Keep refrigerated until serving time.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Remove the large leaves of cabbage (8) and blanch with hot water to soften.
Shred cabbage and slice onion.
Brown in skillet in oleo until golden.
Add salt and pepper to cabbage mixture; then add bread crumbs and put aside to cool.
When cool, add sausage, beef and egg and mix well.
Place a portion in each cabbage leaf and roll.
Tie with a piece of string.
Put on rack in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I place a piece of foil to cover loosely to keep cabbage from burning; remove last 10 minutes.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Put tomatoes into boiling water 1 minute.
Remove tomatoes and peel off skin.
Place tomatoes into kettle and mash.

title: waldorf salad with turkey and apricot
directions: Combine preserves, nonfat yogurt, chopped herbs, mustard, lemon juice, lemon rind, salt and pepper in a large mixing bowl.
Stir with spatula until sauce is well blended.
Add turkey, apples, celery and raisins.
Stir to coat.
Correct seasoning with more salt and pepper as needed.
Place a lettuce cup on each of 6 serving plates.
Spoon a mound of salad on each plate.
Garnish each salad with fresh chopped parsley.
This also makes an excellent sandwich filling for a pita bread pocket.
Makes 6 luncheon servings.

title: strawberry streusel muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture. Set aside.
Combine egg, milk, butter and almond extract. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened. Fold in strawberries. Spoon batter into paper lined muffin pan, filling 3/4 full.
Sprinkle Streusel Topping evenly over batter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.
Yields 1 dozen muffins.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add syrup and remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, longer if necessary.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat sugar and butter; add eggs, then bananas, flour, salt and baking soda.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, salt, spice, eggs and milk. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of cake mix over top.
Spread on pecan halves, then drizzle melted margarine over top.
Make sure all of the dry cake mix is covered with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check after mixture has been in the oven 10 minutes to make certain there are no dry spots, if so put more melted margarine on top.
May be served with whipped cream.
Store remainder of cake mix in plastic bag for later use.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together pumpkin, salt, sugar, pie spice and eggs.
Mix well.
Add evaporated milk and mix well again.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of pumpkin. Sprinkle nuts over top of cake.
Pour melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shish-kabobs
directions: Combine salad dressing, ketchup, mustard, wine, salt and pepper and Worcestershire sauce in large bowl.
Mix well.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Mix in salad dressing and Salad Supreme.
Add vegetables.
Let set overnight.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: On low speed of mixer, blend together peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Slowly add sugar; blend 10 minutes.
Place chocolate chips and wax together and melt.

title: indian tea
directions: Boil 3 cups water and 2 cups sugar for 2 minutes (sugar and water go together).
Mix in 3 lemons, sliced.
Let cool.
Mix all other ingredients in pitcher, then add cooled mixture.
Pour over ice.

title: pumpkin pie(for two 9-inch pies)
directions: Combine pumpkin, eggs, milk, spices and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in two unbaked 9-inch pie crust plates.
Bake at 375°; check after 30 minutes.

title: strufoli(honey clusters)
directions: Cook over low heat.
Add pieces of "cookies" stirring constantly until all pieces are coated.
Remove with slotted spoon and set in refrigerator to chill slightly.
Remove and shape into desired shape and sprinkle with multi-colored sprinkles.

title: quick easy fudge
directions: In medium saucepan on medium heat, mix chocolate chips and sweetened condensed milk until all is melted together.
Turn off heat, add vanilla and nuts.
Put in buttered layer pan. Refrigerate until sets.
Slice into bite size pieces.

title: chicken confetti
directions: Brown chicken and onion in 2 tablespoons oil and add garlic salt in pan.
(I use Dutch oven on top of stove.) Then add tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Stir; simmer until chicken breasts are done (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Cook spaghetti noodles before serving.
Lay noodles on plate with chicken breasts on the side of the plate.
Top both with sauce.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.
Delicious!

title: independence salad
directions: Cut a 1-inch slice from a fresh Georgia watermelon.
Cut the slice in half and remove the rind.
Divide the watermelon into 5 equal wedges and place them in a star pattern with the wide ends together.
There will be an opening in the center; fill this with a generous scoop of cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with fresh Georgia blueberries for a red, white and blue summer salad.

title: granny's potato salad
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes first.
Boil slowly until soft in salted water 20 to 30 minutes.
Chop up onion and place in the bottom of a bowl.
Drain most of the water off the potatoes, but leave about 1/2 cup worth.
Pour HOT potatoes and water on top
of onion and let sit a couple hours.
The heat will take the bitterness out of the onions.
Pour off all the water.
Add chopped celery and the rest.

title: indonesian curried beef
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a large skillet.
Stir ground beef in butter until redness is gone.
Add onion, tomato and green pepper.
Saute until vegetables are tender, but still firm.
Add curry powder.
Stir well and simmer for 1 minute longer.
Serve over brown rice.
Accompanying condiments may be chopped scallions and/or avocados.
Serves four.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into blender container.
Puree until smooth. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large saucepan.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and mace.
Blend in half and half gradually. Stir in broccoli mixture.
Cook until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup butter, lemon juice and rind, chives, garlic and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon onto soup and serve.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Knead 10 minutes.
Let raise until double (about 1 hour). Punch down and shape into loaves.
Let raise and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: coffee punch
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Place ice cream in punch bowl or large pitcher.
Add milk, then hot coffee syrup.
Stir until smooth and serve.	This is a great `punch' for a shower or party!

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all dry ingredients, mixing well. Gradually add water, stirring until smooth over medium heat. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Cook 1 minute, until transparent.

title: waldorf salad dressing
directions: Mix well; let set in refrigerator for several days, the longer the better, even months.
A sweet-sour dressing may be used on fruit salads or cole slaw.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion. Drain. Layer in order given in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve hot with chips.

title: marty's no cook peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt fat.
Brown onion lightly.
Add all other items and simmer 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice bread(any way you slice it, this pumpkin spice bread won't last.)
directions: Heat the oven to 350 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, combine the pumpkin, sugar, water, vegetable oil and eggs. Beat until well mixed. Measure the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, nutmeg and ground cloves into separate bowl, then stir until combined (a great job for kids). Slowly add the dry ingredients to the pumpkin mixture, beating until smooth. Grease two 9- by 5-inch loaf pans and dust them with flour. Evenly divide the batter between the two pans. Bake for 60 to 70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 to 15 minutes. Then remove from pans by inverting them onto a rack and tapping the bottoms. Slice and serve plain, buttered or with cream cheese.

title: honey mustard tenderloin
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Coat tenderloin with mixture. Place on preheated gas grill at medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes, basing occasionally, until meat thermometer registers 155°.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions and peppers with salt in vinegar and water.
Yields 6 pints.

title: overnight salad
directions: Drain the beans, corn and peas.
Chop the celery, peppers and onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together and set overnight in refrigerator.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: farmer's cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients into a bowl.
Add the next 3 ingredients into the bowl.
Mix well.
Then add your cup of instant coffee.
Blend together.
Pour into a greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green chilies. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: grilled deer steaks
directions: Remove all
silver
skin
from backstrap.
Slice across the grain into 1
inch
thick
steaks.
With
point of butcher knife, pierce holes in both sides of steaks.
Place in shallow pan and pour
Italian dressing over steaks.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or
overnight.
Generously
season
with Creole seasoning and black pepper.
Cook over hot coals, turning once until desired doneness.

title: dilled yogurt dressing
directions: Process all ingredients in a blender until the onion is completely pureed.
Makes about 2 cups for any vegetable dish or salad.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and beat at medium speed on electric mixer.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425°
for 35 minutes.

title: cheese and mushrooms
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter; add mushrooms and cook until tender.
In greased casserole (2-quart), layer half of the bread, half the mushroom mix and the cheese.
Repeat the layers with the other half of the bread, mushroom mix and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour evenly over bread mix.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
